      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7911</guid>
      <description>It was a bullish week.  I&amp;#8217;m not sure how much longer it will continue.  Friday&amp;#8217;s action would suggest a weak Monday. The problem with the move off the lows has been volume.  That can resolve itself.  The real test will &amp;#8230; &lt;a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-for-the-week-of-ocotber-10th/"&gt;Continue reading &lt;span class="meta-nav"&gt;&amp;#8594;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/range-traders/Range_Traders-Charts_Data_Analysis_For_The_Week_Of_Ocotber_10th.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>It was a bullish week.  I&#8217;m not sure how much longer it will continue.  Friday&#8217;s action would suggest a weak Monday.</p>
<p>The problem with the move off the lows has been volume.  That can resolve itself.  The real test will come after the first pullback.  The market may have started that process.</p>
<p><span id="more-7911"></span>Trading could be confined between the recent low and the 50d moving average.  It <em>could</em> continue like this for months.</p>
<h1>The magic number of the S&amp;P is 1250.  Price above that number may signal a continued bull move.  The determination will come after the first pullback.  I&#8217;ll be gauging the length in time and the depth of the retreat.  That will help determine the next target and give me clues to the pattern.</h1>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/SP-9th.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7912" title="S&amp;P 9th" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/SP-9th-300x277.png" alt="" width="300" height="277" /></a>Unless your trading is short-term and intraday I&#8217;d be out. .</p>
<p>** Posting will be sporadic this week.  I need to concentrate on implementing the remedies to restore this site to full functionality.  If something dramatic happens I&#8217;ll post, but you can always follow me on Twitter &#8212; RangeTrader2010.  I&#8217;ve been posting mid-morning tweets to assist those of you trading intraday and will continue to call the levels this week.</p>
<p>Thanks for your understanding.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
