      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7902</guid>
      <description>Today may have marked an important short-term low.  I made note of my bottom target, here. Make no mistake, this market is in a severe downtrend.  It will take days and weeks to reverse the pattern.  The worse case scenario &amp;#8230; &lt;a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/tonights-market-update/tonights-market-update-tuesday-4th/"&gt;Continue reading &lt;span class="meta-nav"&gt;&amp;#8594;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/range-traders/Range_Traders-Tonights_Market_Update__Tuesday_4th.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Today may have marked an important short-term low.  I made note of my bottom target, <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/tonights-market-update/tonights-market-update-monday-3rd/">here</a>.</p>
<p>Make no mistake, this market is in a severe downtrend.  It will take days and weeks to reverse the pattern.  The worse case scenario is that the market could stay down at this level and trade sideways for months.</p>
<p><span id="more-7902"></span>Of course, it&#8217;s possible to trade the swings and make money.  I&#8217;d feel more comfortable if the volatility would calm a bit.</p>
<p>With the VIX running high the better strategy is to lessen the time frame and take profits quickly.  A simple strategy that has merit is trading with the 50d MA on a ten minute chart.</p>
<p>Go long when price closes above the 50 and short when it closes below it.  Do this on an intraday basis and don&#8217;t hold positions overnight.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/SP-4th.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7903" title="S&amp;P 4th" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/SP-4th-300x217.png" alt="" width="300" height="217" /></a>Tomorrow&#8217;s action is a tough call.  Price could retrace a bit.  I would hope it wouldn&#8217;t violate the 1079 low.  The first area of resistance for the S&amp;P may be near the 1150 level.</p>
<p>These are interesting times and tough charts to analyze.  Be cautious.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
