      <category><![CDATA[Charts, Data, Analysis]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[market analysis]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[market data]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[range traders]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[range trading]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[stock charts]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7886</guid>
      <description>Miserable.  That just about sums up the market this past week and quarter.  Without question this is a &amp;#8220;stand aside&amp;#8221; kind of market. It&amp;#8217;s futile to analyze sectors and equities.  They are all a mess. With the exception of a &amp;#8230; &lt;a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-for-the-week-beginning-october-3rd/"&gt;Continue reading &lt;span class="meta-nav"&gt;&amp;#8594;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/range-traders/Range_Traders-Charts_Data_Analysis_For_The_Week_Beginning_October_3rd.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/DJ-2.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7888" title="DJ 2" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/DJ-2-300x259.png" alt="Range Trading" width="300" height="259" /></a><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/SP-2.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7889" title="S&amp;P 2" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/SP-2-300x257.png" alt="Range trade" width="300" height="257" /></a><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/SP21.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7892" title="S&amp;P2" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/SP21-300x257.png" alt="range trading" width="300" height="257" /></a><span id="more-7886"></span>Miserable.  That just about sums up the market this past week and quarter.  Without question this is a &#8220;stand aside&#8221; kind of market.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s futile to analyze sectors and equities.  They are all a mess.</p>
<p>With the exception of a very few small, quick trades, I&#8217;m in cash.  It&#8217;s better to sit it out and wait for a trend.</p>
<p>When the VIX is at such high levels 2-4% swings in either direction are possible.  Get caught on the wrong side and you&#8217;ll kick yourself.</p>
<h1>Earnings season is coming.  The market is looking very weak and is testing the range trading support zones.  This isn&#8217;t good.  With the VIX in the stratosphere and a falling market any hiccup will be recorded in dramatic fashion.</h1>
<p>What&#8217;s worse is the market analysts and pundits who keep advising participation in equities.  Wrong!  Take a look at a copper and oil chart.  These commodities are sending different signals.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Copper.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7893" title="Copper" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Copper-300x242.png" alt="" width="300" height="242" /></a><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Oil.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7894" title="Oil" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Oil-300x221.png" alt="" width="300" height="221" /></a></p>
<p>The European debacle will only get worse.  The can has been kicked down the road and now there&#8217;s no more road.</p>
<p>Make no mistake, the world&#8217;s economies are in lockstep heading toward a global recession despite what the market analysts, politicians, and world leaders are saying.</p>
<p>For the average investor my best advice is to protect your resources, stay in cash.</p>
<h2>If you&#8217;re aggressive and want to play, the short side is the better choice.  Just be warned that the wild swings between range trading zones will chew your capital to shreds.  You must be able to withstand the gyrations between one day&#8217;s euphoria and the next day&#8217;s despair.</h2>
<p>This miserable market environment will pass, but not anytime soon.</p>
<h3><em><strong>Believe what you see &#8212; the range trading charts, not what you hear &#8212; TV market chatter.</strong></em></h3>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
