      <description>When the market trades sideways in big swings the best method I&amp;#8217;ve found to make money is to reduce the time frame.  That&amp;#8217;s what I did today. I traded the SPY short and rode it down to my first profit &amp;#8230; &lt;a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/tonights-market-update/tonights-market-update-wednesday-28th/"&gt;Continue reading &lt;span class="meta-nav"&gt;&amp;#8594;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/range-traders/Range_Traders-Tonights_Market_Update__Wednesday_28th.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>When the market trades sideways in big swings the best method I&#8217;ve found to make money is to reduce the time frame.  That&#8217;s what I did today.</p>
<p>I traded the SPY short and rode it down to my first profit target.  There I covered 1/2 of the position.  The trade continued lower and I still have 1/2 of the position remaining.</p>
<p><span id="more-7878"></span><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP-28th.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7879" title="S&amp;P 28th" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP-28th-300x216.png" alt="Market Update" width="300" height="216" /></a></p>
<p>Will it hit the lower target?  Not sure, but this market isn&#8217;t currently controlled by the bulls.</p>
<p>The stair steps down, encased between blue lines, looks likely to continue.  I&#8217;ll know more in the morning and will tweet if something looks tradeable.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
