      <description>The big two day rally &amp;#8212; what caused it?  What has changed? Nothing.  This looks like end of the month window dressing.  The big boys that got caught holding longs are likely trying to get out at the expense of &amp;#8230; &lt;a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/tonights-market-update/tonights-market-update-tuesday-27th/"&gt;Continue reading &lt;span class="meta-nav"&gt;&amp;#8594;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/range-traders/Range_Traders-Tonights_Market_Update__Tuesday_27th.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The big two day rally &#8212; what caused it?  What has changed?</p>
<p>Nothing.  This looks like end of the month window dressing.  The big boys that got caught holding longs are likely trying to get out at the expense of the uninformed trader.</p>
<p><span id="more-7874"></span>This is no market to hold positions &#8212; this is a flippers&#8217; market.  The short squeeze will embolden some market commentators to jump on CNBC and make a bull call for the year&#8217;s end.  Really?</p>
<p>Today, the smokescreen cleared a bit.  My 1180 S&amp;P level was exceeded and a run at  the 1198 level was attempted, but failed.</p>
<p>I feel more confident trading the indexes rather than stocks.  The index patterns are easier to follow while many stocks are off in their own world tracing patterns that make no sense.</p>
<p>Tomorrow looks like a go short day.  I&#8217;ll trade the S&amp;P below today&#8217;s low down to the first support level at 1156.  My next target is support at 1146.  Those levels are drawn on this 10 minute S&amp;P chart.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP-27th.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7875" title="S&amp;P 27th" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP-27th-300x218.png" alt="" width="300" height="218" /></a></p>
]]></content:encoded>
