      <description>This move may go as high as 1180ish in the S&amp;#38;P.  It&amp;#8217;s still a very choppy, sideways pattern. The higher dashed white line represents the 1180 area that may be resistance.  The lower dashed white line may be where price &amp;#8230; &lt;a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/tonights-market-update/tonights-market-update-monday-26th/"&gt;Continue reading &lt;span class="meta-nav"&gt;&amp;#8594;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/range-traders/Range_Traders-Tonights_Market_Update__Monday_26th.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>This move may go as high as 1180ish in the S&amp;P.  It&#8217;s still a very choppy, sideways pattern.</p>
<p><span id="more-7871"></span>The higher dashed white line represents the 1180 area that may be resistance.  The lower dashed white line may be where price corrects, but it&#8217;s too to tell.  This pattern has the look of a completed 5 wave pattern ending in a truncated 5th wave.  The most important question yet to be answered is if this new structure is a wave 1 or an A.</p>
<p>More hand-sitting until the path becomes more clear.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP-26th.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7872" title="S&amp;P 26th" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP-26th-300x161.png" alt="Range Traders" width="300" height="161" /></a></p>
