    <item>
      <title>Charts, Data, Analysis For The Week Beginning September 26</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-for-the-week-beginning-september-26/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-for-the-week-beginning-september-26/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sat, 24 Sep 2011 17:28:50 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Charts, Data, Analysis]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[stock charts]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[stock data]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[stock market analysis]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7857</guid>
      <description>I&amp;#8217;m watching very few charts this week.  My focus is on the two indexes I&amp;#8217;ve identified as leading the overall price patterns. Although modestly higher after a rocky start on Friday, the environment is still very precarious.  It will take &amp;#8230; &lt;a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-for-the-week-beginning-september-26/"&gt;Continue reading &lt;span class="meta-nav"&gt;&amp;#8594;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/range-traders/Range_Traders-Charts_Data_Analysis_For_The_Week_Beginning_September_26.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I&#8217;m watching very few charts this week.  My focus is on the <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/tonights-market-update/tonights-market-update-monday-19/">two indexes</a> I&#8217;ve identified as leading the overall price patterns.</p>
<p>Although modestly higher after a rocky start on Friday, the environment is still very precarious.  It will take a few days of trading to clarify the pattern.</p>
<p>First, let me show the chart of the leading pattern and then compare it to the other indexes.</p>
<p><span id="more-7857"></span>Here&#8217;s one of the two charts that seems to be leading the overall pattern the market is tracing.  I can see 4 waves, but what I can&#8217;t see is if the 4th wave is complete.  The horizontal red and green bars mark the minimum retracement and resistance price range.  What is missing is this: price hasn&#8217;t broken below the last low (white arrow).  That tells me that this chart may still be correcting.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/NDX-22nd.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7858" title="NDX 22nd" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/NDX-22nd-300x276.png" alt="Range Trading" width="300" height="276" /></a>This is the same NDX chart, but it&#8217;s a 10 minute time frame.  Again, price is still above the last low, has made a lower high, and hasn&#8217;t broken the upside barrier (grey dashed line).</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/NDX-10m.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7859" title="NDX 10m" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/NDX-10m-300x216.png" alt="Range Traders" width="300" height="216" /></a>The other leading index, the SOX is doing the same kind of dance, but hasn&#8217;t broken the last low.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SOX-22nd.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7860" title="SOX 22nd" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SOX-22nd-300x189.png" alt="Range Trading" width="300" height="189" /></a>Now let&#8217;s look at the S&amp;P 500 &#8211;</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP-233.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7864" title="S&amp;P 23" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP-233-300x275.png" alt="" width="300" height="275" /></a></p>
<p>The S&amp;P <em><strong>did</strong></em> break the prior low.  That suggests that the 4th wave has ended!</p>
<p>But on this 10 minute chart the S&amp;P has not retraced high enough to say with confidence that the 5th wave down has begun.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP-10m.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7865" title="S&amp;P 10m" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP-10m-300x205.png" alt="" width="300" height="205" /></a>This is another head-scratching moment.  The answer will come in a few days. With certainty I can say this market is not bullish even though the short-term timer(3 moving averages) gave a buy signal last week.</p>
<p>The McClellan Summation index has been decidedly bearish and has resumed its hook to the downside.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/McCl.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7866" title="McCl" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/McCl-300x228.png" alt="" width="300" height="228" /></a>Dr. Copper is<em><strong> not</strong></em> forecasting sunny weather . . . what a tumble!</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Dr.-Copper.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7867" title="Dr. Copper" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Dr.-Copper-300x273.png" alt="" width="300" height="273" /></a>Look at bonds &#8212; jumping out of that bullish wedge and gapping higher.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Bonds1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7868" title="Bonds" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Bonds1-300x276.png" alt="" width="300" height="276" /></a></p>
<p>These are the important aspects to focus on in this market.  Get the patterns right and success will follow.</p>
<p>No amount of sector or stock gazing will provide any better insights about what to do with your money than watching what I&#8217;ve illustrated in this post.</p>
<p>Have a good weekend!</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
