      <title>Tonight’s Market Update — Tuesday 20th</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/tonights-market-update/tonights-market-update-tuesday-20th/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/tonights-market-update/tonights-market-update-tuesday-20th/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Wed, 21 Sep 2011 03:33:27 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Tonight's Market Update]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[range traders]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[range trading]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[stock market update]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=113</guid>
      <description>Five up days and the market has held its ground. This still looks like a 4th wave a-b-c-d-e and this e wave is strong.  If the pattern holds price should not fall below the 1170ish area on the S&amp;#38;P. The &amp;#8230; &lt;a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/tonights-market-update/tonights-market-update-tuesday-20th/"&gt;Continue reading &lt;span class="meta-nav"&gt;&amp;#8594;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/range-traders/Range_Traders-Tonights_Market_Update__Tuesday_20th.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Five up days and the market has held its ground. This still looks like a 4th wave a-b-c-d-e and this e wave is strong.  If the pattern holds price should not fall below the 1170ish area on the S&amp;P.</p>
<p>The first upside target is the high on September 16 at 1220.  The second one is the August 31st 1230 high.</p>
<p><span id="more-113"></span>Price was rebuffed at the 50d MA.  The orange arrow marks the 1170 support area.  Price should not enter the top yellow dashed line.  That is the bottom of wave 1.  If this is wave 4 it should not close in that area.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP-20th.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-114" title="S&amp;P 20th" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP-20th-300x276.png" alt="Market Update Range Trading" width="300" height="276" /></a>Remember<a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-for-the-week-beginning-september-19/"> the indexes that I&#8217;ve flagged as leading the pattern?</a>  Here&#8217;s an update that may offer some clues . . .</p>
<p>Look what happened as price pierced the bottom of wave 1 &#8212; it was rejected and closed below it.  This may be significant if price stays away from that area.  If price does get into the area occupied by wave 1 then the count from the bottom of early August may need reevaluation.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/NDX-20th.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-115" title="NDX 20th" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/NDX-20th-300x277.png" alt="" width="300" height="277" /></a>This chart looks very bullish &#8212; price is rising steeply and is above both the 50 and 200d moving averages.  The longer this bearish wedge continues it seems to argue for a diminished 5th wave down.</p>
<p>This is tricky stuff, but a few more days will offer some clarity.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
