    <item>
      <title>Tonight’s Market Update: Monday 19</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/tonights-market-update/tonights-market-update-monday-19/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/tonights-market-update/tonights-market-update-monday-19/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Tue, 20 Sep 2011 03:55:04 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Tonight's Market Update]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=107</guid>
      <description>The market is giving clues that it wants to move higher.  The Put/Call&amp;#8211;NASDAQ spread shows that option traders are moving into calls (that&amp;#8217;s why the green line is turning higher). That&amp;#8217;s short-term bullish for the market. What&amp;#8217;s not so bullish &amp;#8230; &lt;a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/tonights-market-update/tonights-market-update-monday-19/"&gt;Continue reading &lt;span class="meta-nav"&gt;&amp;#8594;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/range-traders/Range_Traders-Tonights_Market_Update-_Monday_19.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The market is giving clues that it wants to move higher.  The Put/Call&#8211;NASDAQ spread shows that option traders are moving into calls (that&#8217;s why the green line is turning higher). That&#8217;s short-term bullish for the market.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Spread.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-108" title="Spread" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Spread-300x269.png" alt="Range Trading" width="300" height="269" /></a></p>
<p><span id="more-107"></span>What&#8217;s not so bullish is the VIX which is still at the 30ish level.  That means the potential exists for headline risk and quick, sharp moves.</p>
<p>Equities will have a struggle as long as the only commodity with a Phd. in economics,  Dr. Copper, continues his slide, and &#8211;</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Copper1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-109" title="Copper" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Copper1-300x225.png" alt="Range Traders" width="300" height="225" /></a>Treasuries continue to climb breaking to a new high today.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Bonds.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-110" title="Bonds" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Bonds-300x271.png" alt="" width="300" height="271" /></a>Tonight&#8217;s futures are soft after the S&amp;P downgrade of Italy&#8217;s debt.  Expect early morning weakness.  The truth will be told at tomorrow&#8217;s close.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
