    <item>
      <title>Charts, Data, Analysis For The Week Beginning September 19</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-for-the-week-beginning-september-19/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-for-the-week-beginning-september-19/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sat, 17 Sep 2011 17:47:21 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Charts, Data, Analysis]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[market data]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[stock charts]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[stock market analysis]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=96</guid>
      <description>Friday&amp;#8217;s witching day ended a week&amp;#8217;s worth of gains.  It was the best string of green days since the June 27th to July 7th run. Volume was tepid.  Advancers barely led decliners by day&amp;#8217;s end.  The NASDAQ recorded more new &amp;#8230; &lt;a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-for-the-week-beginning-september-19/"&gt;Continue reading &lt;span class="meta-nav"&gt;&amp;#8594;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/range-traders/Range_Traders-Charts_Data_Analysis_For_The_Week_Beginning_September_19.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Friday&#8217;s witching day ended a week&#8217;s worth of gains.  It was the best string of green days since the June 27th to July 7th run.</p>
<p>Volume was tepid.  Advancers barely led decliners by day&#8217;s end.  The NASDAQ recorded more new lows than highs &#8212; 5:3 and the downside volume was modestly higher.</p>
<p>My overall reading of the market is that they are in a corrective short-term upswing.  Overall, the intermediate and long-term forecast is bearish.</p>
<p><span id="more-96"></span>The DJ-30, NASDAQ Composite, and S&amp;P 500 have the same pattern.  I&#8217;ve labeled what appears as the best wave count on the S&amp;P, but it applies to the other indexes, too.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP3.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-97" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP3-300x240.png" alt="Charts, Data, Analysis, Range Traders" width="300" height="240" /></a>A look at some of the key sectors finds:</p>
<p>Gold/silver index (XAU) in a sideways chop &#8211;</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/XAU.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-98" title="XAU" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/XAU-300x194.png" alt="Range Trading Charts Data Analysis" width="300" height="194" /></a>The Oil Index (XOI) looks much like the S&amp;P as it does the sideways dance in a corrective flat pattern:</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Oil.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-99" title="Oil" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Oil-300x193.png" alt="Charts" width="300" height="193" /></a>Copper is considered a leading indicator of global economic health.  It&#8217;s hard to get a read on this chart other than to say that it is surely in a downtrend.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Copper.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-100" title="Copper" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Copper-300x187.png" alt="Data" width="300" height="187" /></a>The long-term Treasury (TLT) has had a nice move and the pattern suggests another move higher, but maybe not before the gap between September 1st and the 2nd fills.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/LT-Treasury.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-101" title="LT Treasury" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/LT-Treasury-300x239.png" alt="Analysis" width="300" height="239" /></a>The VIX is hanging at historically high levels.  Fear is still in the air and that&#8217;s good.  The market likes to climb a wall of worry.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/VIX1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-102" title="VIX" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/VIX1-300x227.png" alt="Range Trading Charts" width="300" height="227" /></a>My favorite breadth indicator, the McClellan Summation index is still hanging out in negative territory.  It has a long climb to get back to the zero line.</p>
<h1><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/McClellan.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-103" title="McClellan" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/McClellan-300x227.png" alt="Range Traders Analysis" width="300" height="227" /></a>Sector Analysis</h1>
<p>The S&amp;P gained 2.5% for the week.  Financials were in the middle of the pack showing a bit of strength over last week&#8217;s dismal performance.  Metals and mining brought up the rear as the equity market absorbed commodity weakness.</p>
<p><span style="color: #008000;">Retail  +4.1%  Tech  4.0  Discretionary  3.8  Industrials  3.1  Financials 2.1  Utilities  1.4  </span></p>
<p><span style="color: #008000;">Oil &amp; Gas Explor/Prod  0.8  Materials  0.6  Staples 0.5  Health Care  0.2 </span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Energy -0.03%  Metals &amp; Mining -1.3</span></p>
<h1><span style="color: #000000;">Bottom Line:</span></h1>
<p>This short-term corrective move may be near an end.  Next week will likely give very good clues.  I&#8217;m thinking that given Friday&#8217;s strength, albeit a quad witch day, the market may gap higher and tag the Range Resistance zone (yellow lines) on this chart.  The 200d MA is hanging out in that area.  It would also coincide with the last high made on August 31st at 1230.71.</p>
<p>If or when that occurs the next bit of head-scratching will begin anew. Price should not climb above the 1260 level.  If it does then my count is off &#8212; a 4th wave should not violate the space occupied by wave 1 (according to Elliot, if I remember correctly).</p>
<p>Here&#8217;s the chart &#8211;</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SPRange-Zone.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-104" title="S&amp;P Range Zone" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SPRange-Zone-300x238.png" alt="" width="300" height="238" /></a>Remember my saying that I thought maybe there was <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/2011/09/13/tonights-market-update-tuesday-13th/">an index giving clues</a> as to direction the market may take?  In fact, there are a couple &#8212; the NDX (NASDAQ 100) and the SOX (Semiconductor index).  I think the NDX is giving the best clues because it has the same bearish wedge as do the S&amp;P and the DJ-30.  The SOX formed a flat corrective pattern.  I&#8217;m watching both.  Here&#8217;s what I see using the NDX &#8211;</p>
<p>If I have this counted correctly the e leg of this corrective 4th wave has already exceeded the high of wave c.  It&#8217;s moving quickly toward the Range Resistance zone and a possible completion of the bearish wedge.</p>
<p>This move should not exceed the white line, the bottom of wave 1. Watch and see if price exceeds or recedes at 2318.64.  That <em>may</em> tell us that wave 5 down has begun.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/NDX-Leader.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-105" title="NDX Leader" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/NDX-Leader-300x239.png" alt="Range Trading Analysis" width="300" height="239" /></a></p>
<h1>Watch List:</h1>
<p>I want to catch the move down, so I&#8217;ve prepared a watch list of potential shorting candidates.  In no particular order &#8211;</p>
<p>CAH, ZION, HOT HON, WLP ,ALTR, APD, ARG, ADP, BEN, DHR, LH, MKC, MYL, PGR, PPG, CHRW, SIAL, UTX, CTXS, IR, MRK, SNA, ORCL, ZMH</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;"><br />
</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
