      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Tonight's Market Update]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=85</guid>
      <description>The market is sending double signals: gold, bonds, and currencies are trading on fear while stocks have found a bid.  Even the following chart of the Stock Timer shows that it wants to turn positive. The market is caught in &amp;#8230; &lt;a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/tonights-market-update/tonights-market-update-wednesday-14th/"&gt;Continue reading &lt;span class="meta-nav"&gt;&amp;#8594;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/range-traders/Range_Traders-Tonights_Market_Update__Wednesday_14th.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The market is sending double signals: gold, bonds, and currencies are trading on fear while stocks have found a bid.  Even the following chart of the Stock Timer shows that it wants to turn positive.</p>
<p><span id="more-85"></span><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Stock-Timer.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-86" title="Stock Timer" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Stock-Timer-300x208.png" alt="" width="300" height="208" /></a>The market is caught in a range that is forming a bearish wedge.  Not my kind of market to trade.  For those that like this type of environment the top of the blue line on the next chart is probably a good &#8220;get out of Dodge&#8221; sell point.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP-Hourly.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-87" title="S&amp;P Hourly" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP-Hourly-300x135.png" alt="Range Trader" width="300" height="135" /></a>Don&#8217;t forget this chart two and the two pink lines.  Twice price has failed at the first one, but I expect it will power up to the higher one.  The 50d MA is looking down from above, too.  Lots of overhead resistance should give long-term traders reason to pause and think.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP14th.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-88" title="S&amp;P14th" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP14th-300x268.png" alt="Range Trader" width="300" height="268" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
