    <item>
      <title>Tonight’s Market Update — Tuesday 13th</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/tonights-market-update/tonights-market-update-tuesday-13th/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/tonights-market-update/tonights-market-update-tuesday-13th/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Wed, 14 Sep 2011 04:08:41 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Tonight's Market Update]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=80</guid>
      <description>The intermediate trend is still down.  Be cautious. This is a great time to build a watch list of stocks that are holding up despite the downtrend.  Those equities are the ones likely to be the first movers when this &amp;#8230; &lt;a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/tonights-market-update/tonights-market-update-tuesday-13th/"&gt;Continue reading &lt;span class="meta-nav"&gt;&amp;#8594;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/range-traders/Range_Traders-Tonights_Market_Update__Tuesday_13th.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The intermediate trend is still down.  Be cautious.</p>
<p>This is a great time to build a watch list of stocks that are holding up despite the downtrend.  Those equities are the ones likely to be the first movers when this slide ends.</p>
<p>The following hourly S&amp;P chart shows where I think we are in the pattern.  It looks like this is the fourth wave (read uptrend) and it&#8217;s working on the E leg.  The E leg should take price above the C wave of the 4th wave.  In other words, price should exceed the last high before resuming the downtrend or 5th wave.</p>
<p><span id="more-80"></span>That would also complete the bearish wedge formation.  Once price exceeds the August 31st high price will likely start to retreat.  A 5th wave is in progress when the low marked by the arrow near D, is broken.  The ultimate test for a confirmed 5th leg down will be when the low is broken at point B &#8212; 1121 on the S&amp;P.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP-waves.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-81" title="S&amp;P waves" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP-waves-300x216.png" alt="Range Trading" width="300" height="216" /></a>If you&#8217;ve followed my work you know that I look to find an index showing leadership.  I think I&#8217;ve found the one that is blazing the way.  I&#8217;ll show you what I&#8217;ve found in a future post.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s getting late here on the left coast and the Wednesday morning futures are looking very red.  See you tomorrow.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Futures-Wed-morn.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-82" title="Futures Wed morn" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Futures-Wed-morn-300x139.png" alt="Range Trader" width="300" height="139" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
