    <item>
      <title>Tonight’s Market Update — Monday 12th</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/tonights-market-update/tonights-market-update-monday-12th/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/tonights-market-update/tonights-market-update-monday-12th/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Tue, 13 Sep 2011 03:38:15 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Tonight's Market Update]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=75</guid>
      <description>In any other environment the end-of-the-day rally would have been impressive.  In this market it looks like a bit of relief after a hard, two day slide. Price probed below the 78.6 retracement of the move from the August low &amp;#8230; &lt;a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/tonights-market-update/tonights-market-update-monday-12th/"&gt;Continue reading &lt;span class="meta-nav"&gt;&amp;#8594;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/range-traders/Range_Traders-Tonights_Market_Update__Monday_12th.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In any other environment the end-of-the-day rally would have been impressive.  In this market it looks like a bit of relief after a hard, two day slide.</p>
<p>Price probed below the 78.6 retracement of the move from the August low to the August high.  I think we can be assured those lows will be challenged.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP-M.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-76" title="S&amp;P M" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP-M-300x277.png" alt="Range Traders" width="300" height="277" /></a></p>
<p><span id="more-75"></span>Today&#8217;s nice move into the plus column sets up a nice short squeeze.  Until the underpinnings of this market improve all rallies will be hammered.  For example, look at all of these top-of-the-range closes.  Most were beaten back within a day or two.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP-top-range-closes.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-77" title="S&amp;P top range closes" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP-top-range-closes-300x236.png" alt="Range Trading" width="300" height="236" /></a>Here&#8217;s an hourly chart.  Notice the sideways nature and how price is trading firmly below the double yellow range support (now resistance) lines.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP-hrly.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-78" title="S&amp;P hrly" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP-hrly-300x235.png" alt="Range Traders" width="300" height="235" /></a>Keep your eye on the red arrow and the blue boxes mentioned <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/2011/09/11/futures-for-monday/">HERE</a>.  I think they will be of interest before this sideways pattern ends.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
