    <item>
      <title>Charts, Data, Analysis For The Week Beginning September 12th</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-for-the-week-beginning-september-12th/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-for-the-week-beginning-september-12th/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sat, 10 Sep 2011 18:15:35 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Charts, Data, Analysis]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[charts]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[data]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[market analysis]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=51</guid>
      <description>It seems that every weekend the market commentary is simply a repeat of the previous one.  This is a glum market that is showing no sign of improvement.  In my estimation, smart money should be on the sidelines and in &amp;#8230; &lt;a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-for-the-week-beginning-september-12th/"&gt;Continue reading &lt;span class="meta-nav"&gt;&amp;#8594;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/range-traders/Range_Traders-Charts_Data_Analysis_For_The_Week_Beginning_September_12th.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>It seems that every weekend the market commentary is simply a repeat of the previous one.  This is a glum market that is showing no sign of improvement.  In my estimation, smart money should be on the sidelines and in cash.  That&#8217;s where the big player&#8217;s are sitting.  They show no confidence in this market and are not committing fresh capital.  The upswings are simply short-covering rallies.</p>
<p>Here&#8217;s where the major averages stand.  All are in sync and flailing around like a helpless, beached, trout.</p>
<p><span id="more-51"></span><em>The S&amp;P &#8211;</em></p>
<h1>This weekly chart shows how the personality of this and all of the averages changed when the long-term trend line (white line) was broken to the downside.  The yellow box is a Range Zone of support.  Price will likely enter that zone and stabilize before the next move.  Notice, too, how the volume bars on the far right are predominately red.  The selling pressure overwhelms any buying and quickly sends price lower.</h1>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP2.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-52" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP2-300x237.png" alt="Range trading" width="300" height="237" /></a>The same S&amp;P daily chart, with a closer view, magnifies the chop.  I also see a bearish wedge.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SPbw.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-53" title="S&amp;Pbw" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SPbw-300x240.png" alt="Range trading" width="300" height="240" /></a>The DJ-30 has a nearly identical pattern.  The NASDAQ Composite is super choppy.  Notice all of the island gaps both up and down on this daily chart.  Despite the super-chop a bearish wedge is present here, too.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/NAZ4.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-56" title="NAZ" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/NAZ4-300x239.png" alt="Range Trader" width="300" height="239" /></a></p>
<p>The VIX remains stubbornly high.  That tells me that the wide and wild swings will continue.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/VIX.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-57" title="VIX" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/VIX-300x226.png" alt="Range Trading" width="300" height="226" /></a></p>
<p>The long bond has had a dramatic rise and shows no sign of slowing.  That denotes a flight to safety even though the yield is paltry.</p>
<p>When money starts to flow out of bonds then it will be time to watch equities for a potential bottom.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Bond1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-59" title="Bond" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Bond1-300x272.png" alt="Range Trading Zones" width="300" height="272" /></a></p>
<p>I&#8217;m inclined to think that a visit back to the recent lows is probably coming.</p>
<p>This is not my kind of market in which to invest.  The wide swing days and the extreme chop make for a money meat-grinder.  I will be patient and wait for the conditions that suit my style of trading before I commit hard-earned moolah.</p>
<h2><em>Sectors:</em></h2>
<p>The S&amp;P was down -1.68% for the week.  Retail was the only green sector, but only by a bit.  Financials continue to lead to the downside, a very bearish sign.</p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Financials  -2.4%  Materials  2.3  Industrials 2.1  Discretionary 1.7  Health Care 1.4</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Utilities  1.4  Staples  1.1  Metals and Mining  1.1 Oil and Gas Exploration &amp; Production  0.7</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #339966;"><span style="color: #ff0000;">Technology  0.5</span>  Retail  +0.7%</span></p>
<p><em><strong>The Bottom Line:</strong></em></p>
<p>It&#8217;s a lot easier to make money in a trending market.  Be patient as this market chops around and decides where to find a bottom.  It may be a while.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
