      <pubDate>Thu, 08 Sep 2011 03:47:01 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Tonight's Market Update]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=35</guid>
      <description>Both the S&amp;#38;P 500 and the NASDAQ broke the first Range Resistance barriers. The DJ-30 didn&amp;#8217;t. The Dow needs to get past that closest pink line and then make a run for the higher of  the two horizontal lines. The &amp;#8230; &lt;a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/tonights-market-update/todays-market-update/"&gt;Continue reading &lt;span class="meta-nav"&gt;&amp;#8594;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/range-traders/Range_Traders-Tonights_Market_Update.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Both the S&amp;P 500 and the NASDAQ broke the first Range Resistance barriers.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-38" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP1-300x276.png" alt="Range Trader" width="300" height="276" /></a><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/NAZ.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-39" title="NAZ" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/NAZ-300x277.png" alt="Range Trading" width="300" height="277" /></a><span id="more-35"></span>The DJ-30 didn&#8217;t.</p>
<p>The Dow needs to get past that closest pink line and then make a run for the higher of  the two horizontal lines.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/DJ.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-37" title="DJ" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/DJ-300x276.png" alt="Range Trading" width="300" height="276" /></a>The market is trying to put in a bottom.  Short-term things look much better, but the overall technicals are still a mess.  Watch for a bond market sell-off for a clue that this might turn into something more sustainable than a one or two day rally.  Maybe then the focus can turn to higher Range Resistance levels mentioned <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/2011/09/07/range-trading-zones-for-wednesday/">here.</a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
