      <title>Charts, Data, Analysis For The Week Beginning September 6th</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-for-the-week-beginning-september-6th/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-for-the-week-beginning-september-6th/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Mon, 05 Sep 2011 16:43:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Charts, Data, Analysis]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7823</guid>
      <description>It&amp;#8217;s been a long weekend trying to get the blog up and running after software conflicts and a back door attack.  I&amp;#8217;ll be extending memberships as my way of compensating for your patience.  Just drop me an email and I&amp;#8217;ll &amp;#8230; &lt;a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-for-the-week-beginning-september-6th/"&gt;Continue reading &lt;span class="meta-nav"&gt;&amp;#8594;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/range-traders/Range_Traders-Charts_Data_Analysis_For_The_Week_Beginning_September_6th.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>It&#8217;s been a long weekend trying to get the blog up and running after software conflicts and a back door attack.  I&#8217;ll be extending memberships as my way of compensating for your patience.  Just drop me an email and I&#8217;ll tick the box next to your membership.  Now,  on to the charts!</p>
<p>The charts tell the story &#8211;</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SPw1.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-7832 aligncenter" title="S&amp;Pw" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SPw1-300x225.png" alt="Range Trader" width="300" height="225" /></a>The chart above is a weekly S&amp;P shot.  Range line support is close, but there are layers below that might come into play.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/DJw.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7833" title="DJw" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/DJw-300x225.png" alt="Range Trading" width="300" height="225" /></a>I&#8217;ve highlighted the  Range line number to watch on this weekly DJ-30 chart.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/NAZw.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7834" title="NAZw" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/NAZw-300x224.png" alt="Range Traders" width="300" height="224" /></a>Here&#8217;s the NAZ.  Again, I&#8217;ve highlighted the Range support line.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">All three of these charts are in agreement as their patterns are nearly identical.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">It looks like the pattern has formed an irregular top.  In very basic terms that means the last high did not exceed the prior high.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span id="more-7836"></span>The sector action shows that the Financials are leading the way lower.  The worst is probably coming in Europe.  The focus has now included Italy alongside the Greek financial problem.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">These next few month are the worst for the market.  Add a listless economy and the European financial crisis and it looks like a very tough time ahead for the equity market.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">These next charts are a zoom level of daily charts.  Notice the double lines.  These are fib projections.  The most important level to watch, from my experience is the 100% level in blue.  The slide is likely to stop near that area.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">S&amp;P 500 &#8211;</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SPlevels.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7835" title="S&amp;Plevels" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SPlevels-300x268.png" alt="Range Trading" width="300" height="268" /></a>DJ-30 &#8211;</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/DJlevels.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7836" title="DJlevels" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/DJlevels-300x270.png" alt="Range Trader" width="300" height="270" /></a>NAZ &#8211;</p>
<h2 style="text-align: left;">Sectors:</h2>
<p style="text-align: left;">The Friday fall put the S&amp;P in the red &#8212; -0.24.  The other sectors stack up like this:</p>
<p><span style="color: #339966;">Oil and Gas Exploration/Production  +1.2%</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #339966;">Metals  0.95</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #339966;">Utilities  0.88</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #339966;">Health Care  0.65</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #339966;">Energy 0.62</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #339966;">Staples 0.56</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #339966;">Materials 0.12</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Discretionary -0.17%</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Industrials  0.26</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Retail  0.55</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Technology  0.76</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Financials  1.8</span></p>
<h1>The Bottom Line:</h1>
<p>Aggressive traders may want to short the indexes and cover a partial position at the 100% blue line seen on the charts.  Otherwise, cash is king.  It looks like this is going to stay ugly.</p>
