    <item>
      <title>Back Up And Running</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/back-up-and-running/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/back-up-and-running/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Thu, 01 Sep 2011 19:46:34 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7788</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Thanks for your patience.  This has been a wild 24 hours and a first for me.  The site was down due to a back door hack that I don&#8217;t completely understand.  Anyway, back to what I know &#8212; the market! &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/back-up-and-running/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Thanks for your patience.  This has been a wild 24 hours and a first for me.  The site was down due to a back door hack that I don&#8217;t completely understand.  Anyway, back to what I know &#8212; the market!</p>
<p>Yesterday&#8217;s market probed higher only to retreat to the bottom of the range.  Volume was decent, but is likely because of scared shorts covering their positions.  This is not a rally stoked with the fresh fuel of new money.</p>
<p>What follows is a two hour chart.  It seems that price wants to return to the first set of Range lines that have now become support.  Breaking through those lines will signal a fresh leg down.  Tomorrow&#8217;s jobs number will likely produce a big reaction.  I&#8217;m not sure which direction.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/range-trading-2/back-up-and-running/attachment/sp-202/" rel="attachment wp-att-7789"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7789" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/SP-300x140.png" alt="Range Lines" width="300" height="140" /></a><span id="more-7788"></span>I think there will be a shorting opportunity within the next week.  It looks like the markets are tracking in a triangle pattern which is a hallmark continuation pattern.  If true, watch for price to break higher one last time.  I say one last time because the move is mature and this is likely a 4th wave.  One last push would create a wave 5.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m going to start a watch list of shorting candidates during the long Labor Day weekend.  I&#8217;ll post them as soon as I put something together.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/back-up-and-running/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
