      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7709</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Nothing has changed.  The market is still consumed with out of control spending sprees and the associated U.S. debt.  No amount of happy talk or big business deals will counter it. Look at the Buffet/Bank of America deal as an &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-28th/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Nothing has changed.  The market is still consumed with out of control spending sprees and the associated U.S. debt.  No amount of happy talk or big business deals will counter it.</p>
<p>Look at the Buffet/Bank of America deal as an example.  BAC rallied hard with the Thursday news that Warren B. had invested a wad of cash.  Price gapped higher and climbed only to close down near the bottom of the day&#8217;s range.  The  institutional  investors  took the gift and sold the entire move on  heavy volume.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7713" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-28th/attachment/bac-2/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7713" title="BAC" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/BAC1-300x274.png" alt="Range Trading" width="300" height="274" /></a></p>
<h1>There&#8217;s no fooling the smart money.</h1>
<p>This coming week is the last full week of trading before the long Labor Day weekend.  Expect more see-saw price movement.</p>
<p><span id="more-7709"></span><strong>Charts:</strong></p>
<p>None  of the major stock averages have made a serious run toward the 200d  MA.  Range zones of support and resistance are well-defined on each.   All three are in lock-step agreement with each other.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-7712" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-28th/attachment/comp-11/"><img class="aligncenter" title="Comp" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Comp1-300x292.png" alt="Range Trading" width="300" height="292" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7711" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-28th/attachment/dj-30-34/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7711" title="DJ 30" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/DJ-301-300x289.png" alt="Range Trading" width="300" height="289" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7712" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-28th/attachment/comp-11/"></a><a rel="attachment wp-att-7714" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-28th/attachment/sp-194/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7714" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/SP24-300x290.png" alt="Range Traders" width="300" height="290" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The VIX is still cruising at lofty levels and is telegraphing the extreme amount of volatility seen in the market.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7715" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-28th/attachment/vix-22/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7715" title="VIX" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/VIX2-300x226.png" alt="Range Traders" width="300" height="226" /></a></p>
<p>After a bit of a retrace gold is reasserting some muscle.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7716" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-28th/attachment/gld-27/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7716" title="GLD" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/GLD2-300x277.png" alt="Range Traders" width="300" height="277" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>I still like SLV even though my trade got stopped.  Price closed at the top of the range on Friday, but there wasn&#8217;t enough volume to give it the necessary strength that I like to see before initiating a trade.  I&#8217;m waiting.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7717" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-28th/attachment/slv-7/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7717" title="SLV" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/SLV2-300x274.png" alt="Range Trading" width="300" height="274" /></a></p>
<p><strong>Sector Action:</strong></p>
<p>The sector&#8217;s tone swung from defensive last week as Utilities led the gains, to a tepid offensive push with Retail in the lead.</p>
<p>The S&amp;P 500 gained 4.74% for the week and all sectors were in the green,too.</p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #339966;">Retail  7.5%</span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #339966;">Industrials  6.1</span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #339966;">Discretionary  6.0</span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #339966;">Materials  6.0</span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #339966;">Metals &amp; Mining 5.9</span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #339966;">Technology  5.6</span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #339966;">Financials  5.2</span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #339966;">Energy  4.0</span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #339966;">Health Care  3.9</span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #339966;">Oil &amp; Gas Exploration/Production  3.6</span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #339966;">Staples  2.1</span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #339966;">Utilities  1.8</span></strong></p>
<p><strong>Statistical Scans:</strong></p>
<p>None</p>
<p><strong>The Bottom Line:</strong></p>
<p>There are opportunities in this market, but they are on a very short time frame.  If you want to participate here&#8217;s an idea for a trading system:  find stocks that move at least 3 points per day and trade at minimum of 1 million shares.  Find a &#8220;minute&#8221; time frame that fits your comfort level, i.e. 5 minute, 15 minute, etc.  Locate the range zones of support and resistance.</p>
<p>Place a long trade just above a range zone of support &#8212; put the stop level just below the same support zone.</p>
<p>Do the opposite to go short.  Find a range resistance zone and go short a bit below it.  Stop the trade just above the resistance zone.</p>
<p>Take partial profits at the next support/resistance level.  Move the stop to that level for the remainder of the trade.  Close all trades by day&#8217;s end.</p>
<p>There is no discernable trend in this market.  I&#8217;m watching the metals, especially silver, for another entry.  Even then I&#8217;m afraid the stops will need to be wide to catch  and sty in an up move.</p>
<p>There are times to be in the market and times to be out of it.  Sideline times  provide an opportunity to study or improve techniques.  That&#8217;s how I&#8217;m spending some of my time &#8212; learning from the greatest of all teachers, Mother Market.</p>
<p>Have a great weekend!</p>
]]></content:encoded>
