      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The averages couldn&#8217;t get it done and ended the session at the bottom of the day&#8217;s range.  Price did probe higher to just beneath the double yellow lines, but quickly retreated.</p>
<p>The pattern on the chart is as undulating as the Loch Ness monster.  The market&#8217;s wild swings make it hard to trade unless your time frame is calculated in minutes.</p>
<p>There is a cup and handle forming on the chart.  The averages need to hold support (white line) at 1150ish on the S&amp;P before we can see a move higher.</p>
<p>Watch the open for a gap higher.  It may be a clue of things to come.</p>
