      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The yellow lines are the first Range Resistance zones.  The red lines are the second layer.  I&#8217;ve thought that the averages may challenge their respective 200d MAs and I still see the possibility.  The red zones are very close to the current position of the 200d moving averages.</p>
<p>Watch for a gap up tomorrow that may foreshadow a bit of strength.  The S&amp;P will likely start hitting bumpy air near the 1187 altitude.</p>
<p>Very light trading volume means no institutional support.  The pros are cautious and that should be a warning that this market remains on shaky ground.</p>
