      <title>The Gap That Couldn't</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/gain/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/gain/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Tue, 23 Aug 2011 04:42:44 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7649</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[The market opened strong and then proceeded to give back the gains.  It was another day when low volume accompanied the move higher. This is a 1 minute chart of the SPY.  Point A shows the gap open and the &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/gain/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The market opened strong and then proceeded to give back the gains.  It was another day when low volume accompanied the move higher.</p>
<p>This is a 1 minute chart of the SPY.  Point A shows the gap open and the immediate move down (point B) culminating in the first low of the day (left most point D).</p>
<p>The market went sideways for most of the afternoon.  At approximately 10 minutes before the close price went down and retested the low made earlier in the day.</p>
<p>The last 4 minutes saw price grapple a few points higher into the end of the session.  The last few minutes of lift created a bearish wedge on the chart (point E).</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7650" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/current-market-news/gain/attachment/spmin/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7650" title="SPmin" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/SPmin-300x173.png" alt="Range Trading" width="300" height="173" /></a></p>
<p>That second low near the end of the day was 5 points lower than the low at 12:00 p.m.  I don&#8217;t think this market will gain much traction until it can stop printing intraday lows.</p>
<p>I took a long trade with SLV this morning.  If  SLV can get past the recent high it looks like a clear shot toward $48.  There will be lots of hammers waiting to hit the SLV nail near that $48 level.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7651" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/current-market-news/gain/attachment/slv-6/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7651" title="SLV" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/SLV1-300x173.png" alt="Range trading" width="300" height="173" /></a></p>
<p><span id="more-7649"></span>You know it&#8217;s a bad day in the market when an up day looks weak.</p>
<p>The market&#8217;s two main themes concerned investors again on Monday: 1)  losses in financials, materials and energy point to global slowdown  fears, and 2) strength in bonds, the VIX and gold show the flight to  safety trade.</p>
<p>You&#8217;ll know we&#8217;re nearing the end of the downturn when  these patterns break down.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m leaning toward a few shorts &#8212; they&#8217;re on the <a href="http://tinyurl.com/4d3tfoc">Trade Sheet.</a></p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/gain/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
