      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7637</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Miserable.  That summarizes last week&#8217;s action fairly well.  This market has plenty of room to move down. These weekly charts tell the story &#8211; DJ 30 has broken below support &#8211; so has the Russell. Gold is flying and very &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-22nd/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Miserable.  That summarizes last week&#8217;s action fairly well.  This market has plenty of room to move down.</p>
<p>These weekly charts tell the story &#8211;</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7638" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-22nd/attachment/comp-10/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7638" title="NAZ Composite" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Comp-300x267.png" alt="" width="300" height="267" /></a></p>
<p>DJ 30 has broken below support &#8211;</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7639" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-22nd/attachment/dj-30-33/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7639" title="DJ 30" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/DJ-30-300x248.png" alt="" width="300" height="248" /></a></p>
<p>so has the Russell.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7640" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-22nd/attachment/rut-32/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7640" title="RUT" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/RUT1-300x222.png" alt="" width="300" height="222" /></a></p>
<p>Gold is flying and very stretched from the moving averages.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7641" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-22nd/attachment/gld-26/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7641" title="GLD" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/GLD1-300x267.png" alt="" width="300" height="267" /></a></p>
<p>The VIX is flying high.</p>
<h1><a rel="attachment wp-att-7642" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-22nd/attachment/vix-21/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7642" title="VIX" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/VIX1-300x226.png" alt="" width="300" height="226" /></a></h1>
<h1>Good news and happy talk may ignite a huge rally, but remember the trend.  <strong><em>The larger trend is down.</em></strong></h1>
<p><span id="more-7637"></span><strong>Sector Analysis</strong></p>
<p>The news is dismal.  Rather than post the numbers I&#8217;ll give you a cut and dried assessment.  The S&amp;P fell 4.6% for the week.  All S&amp;P sectors were hit hard with the exception of two: Consumer Staples and Utilities.  <strong>Staples were flat for the week.  Utilities were higher by 2 percentage points.</strong></p>
<p><strong>Statistical Scans</strong></p>
<p>No data</p>
<p><strong>Bottom Line</strong></p>
<p>The price action on many  of the index charts shows an upthrust bar followed by a down bar.  That confirms weakness.  The junior averages look especially weak after posting a gap down on Thursday&#8217;s open.</p>
<p>Oil is mimicing the move of the major averages.  The US dollar is sideways and gold (the metal, not the miners) looks very stretched as mentioned in the above chart.  <strong> </strong></p>
<h2>This is a no-confidence market &#8212; no confidence in the political leadership, and no confidence fiscally or economically.  Junk bond yields are increasing.  That is further confirmation of risk aversion.  Stocks, bonds, the VIX, gold, and the economies and fiscal policies of Europe and the US point to more bad times a comin&#8217;.</h2>
<p>The calendar is working against the market.  We are fast approaching a very weak time period in September and October.</p>
<p>Will all of this prompt a QE 3 announcement at Jackson Hole?</p>
<p>Misery is misery.  There are really no degrees of the pain.  This is a very unhealthy market.  There are not an abundance of set ups that stir interest.  I will show you one that has caught my eye and let you decide for yourself.  In the meantime, there isn&#8217;t much to do until we see some resolution.  Maybe that happens this next week.</p>
<p>Here&#8217;s one long play I like &#8212; SLV.  It broke above resistance on good volume.  I&#8217;m going to include it on the trade sheet.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7643" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-22nd/attachment/slv-5/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7643" title="SLV" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/SLV-300x253.png" alt="" width="300" height="253" /></a></p>
<p>I want to wait for an up day to consider shorting some of the indexes or buying an inverse ETF like the DXD.  I&#8217;ll let you know when I&#8217;m going to move.</p>
