      <title>Trading The Market's Hurdles</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/market-hurdles/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/market-hurdles/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Tue, 16 Aug 2011 04:53:29 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Trading The Market]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7591</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[For the fifth straight day the market moved higher as investors shrugged at the dismal Empire State Manufacturing number and swiftly traded the market to higher levels. The horizontal lines are two separate sets of strong range line zones of &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/market-hurdles/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>For the fifth straight day the market moved higher as investors shrugged at the dismal Empire State Manufacturing number and swiftly traded the market to higher levels.</p>
<p>The horizontal lines are two separate sets of strong range line zones of resistance.  Tonight  price is barely above the first set.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7592" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/market-hurdles/attachment/sp-183/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7592" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/SP13-300x154.png" alt="" width="300" height="154" /></a></p>
<p>That&#8217;s good, but there are some <strong><em>&#8220;tells&#8221;</em></strong> that aren&#8217;t so good.  The first problem is the bearish wedge that is forming.  That pattern is evident on a lot of charts.</p>
<p>Secondly, volume has declined again showing that the big fellas are backing off from adding more shares.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7597" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/market-hurdles/attachment/spd-7/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7597" title="S&amp;Pd" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/SPd2-300x176.png" alt="" width="300" height="176" /></a></p>
<p>The VIX has retreated from the aether, but is still soaring at lofty levels.  This market is far from being calm and sedate.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7598" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/market-hurdles/attachment/vix-20/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7598" title="VIX" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/VIX-300x145.png" alt="" width="300" height="145" /></a></p>
<p>A pause or shallow pullback would give the market time to work off the exuberance of the last five days.  Tomorrow may be important.</p>
<p><span id="more-7591"></span>Once again a little money in the bank helps the cause in this crazy market environment.  Stops have been updated on the trade sheet.  I&#8217;m not looking to add shares until this market proves its desire to move higher.</p>
<p><a href="http://tinyurl.com/4d3tfoc">Trade Sheet</a></p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/market-hurdles/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
