    <item>
      <title>Charts, Data, Analysis For The Week Of August 15th</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-august-15th/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-august-15th/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sat, 13 Aug 2011 18:48:34 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Charts, Data, Analysis]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[stock charts]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[stock data]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[stock market analysis]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7570</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Thursday and Friday helped recover some of the week&#8217;s damage as seen on this weekly chart. That&#8217;s the good news.  The bad news is that price is still below a confluence of moving averages resting near a range line zone &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-august-15th/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Thursday and Friday helped recover some of the week&#8217;s damage as seen on this weekly chart. That&#8217;s the good news.  The bad news is that price is still below a confluence of moving averages resting near a range line zone of support.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7571" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-august-15th/attachment/spw-2/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7571" title="S&amp;Pw" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/SPw-300x241.png" alt="" width="300" height="241" /></a></p>
<p>Volume was enormous toward the end of the week.  It could be interpreted as a short term capitulation of sellers as fear of short covering dried up the demand.  This daily chart shows the big volume and the subsequent declining volume as price pushed higher.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7573" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-august-15th/attachment/spd-6/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7573" title="S&amp;Pd" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/SPd1-300x241.png" alt="" width="300" height="241" /></a></p>
<p>If price is going to make a run toward the 200d MA I&#8217;d expect a better showing from volume.  That would tell me the shorts are covering and that the institutional players are willing to trade the swing.</p>
<p>Make no mistake, this market has entered a bear phase.  Damage is widespread and severe and all of the indexes &#8212; S&amp;P, NASDAQ, NDX, Russell 2000 are in agreement.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s going to be a tough climb for stocks to scale this wall of worry.</p>
<p><span id="more-7570"></span>The US dollar keeps bumping along beneath the yellow long term trend line.  There is so much politics tied to the currency it&#8217;s a tough call to know how the currency may trade.  If the market falls it wouldn&#8217;t be unexpected to see the dollar rise.  But these aren&#8217;t normal times.  Manipulation has skewed the playing field.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7574" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-august-15th/attachment/dollar-41/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7574" title="Dollar" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Dollar1-300x210.png" alt="" width="300" height="210" /></a></p>
<p>Money coming from stocks fled to the safety of Treasuries.  Notice how the long term bond&#8217;s weekly chart shows a probe to higher levels eclipsing the July high.  Volume powered the bonds higher.  This chart will be key to gauge the health of the equity market in the coming weeks and months.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7575" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-august-15th/attachment/bonds-3/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7575" title="Bonds" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Bonds-300x240.png" alt="" width="300" height="240" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>We&#8217;re not alone in this market mess and economic disaster.  This is London&#8217; exchange &#8211;</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7580" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-august-15th/attachment/ftse/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7580" title="FTSE" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/FTSE-300x213.png" alt="" width="300" height="213" /></a></p>
<p>Frankfurt DAX</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7581" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-august-15th/attachment/f-dax/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7581" title="F DAX" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/F-DAX-300x210.png" alt="" width="300" height="210" /></a>China FTSE</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7582" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-august-15th/attachment/ftse-2/"><a rel="attachment wp-att-7583" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-august-15th/attachment/ftse-3/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7583" title="FTSE" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/FTSE2-300x209.png" alt="" width="300" height="209" /></a><br />
</a>Big problems in equity land and no easy, quick answers.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Sector Analysis:</strong></p>
<p>Here&#8217;s a bullish percent chart last published <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/range-traders/charts-data-analysis-week-2/">July 11th</a>.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7576" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-august-15th/attachment/bp-19/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7576" title="BP" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/BP-300x192.png" alt="" width="300" height="192" /></a></p>
<p>These are the readings for today &#8212; a month later.  The skew has definitely shifted.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7577" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-august-15th/attachment/bp-now/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7577" title="bp now" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/bp-now-300x194.png" alt="" width="300" height="194" /></a></p>
<p>The gloomy fundamental news may trick and trap novice traders in short positions while the market continues to claw its way higher.  Volatility and the associated intraday swings are still going to appear.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m willing to go with the market if it wants to swing higher, but I&#8217;m watching over my shoulder.</p>
<p>There are no Statistical Scans for obvious reasons.  I&#8217;ve hand-picked all of the trades and have a new one for Monday.  Easy does it with the cash on these as this market can make you look silly real fast.</p>
<p>Have a good weekend!</p>
<p><a href="http://tinyurl.com/4d3tfoc">Trade Sheet</a></p>
