      <category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7559</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Did price find the bottom of the range in this waterfall slide?  Maybe.  Price hit the 38.2 retracement of the entire move beginning March &#8217;09 and stopped at that level. Volatility is still key and the big players (institutions) are &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/bottom-range/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Did price find the bottom of the range in this waterfall slide?  Maybe.  Price hit the 38.2 retracement of the entire move beginning March &#8217;09 and stopped at that level.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7560" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/range-trading-2/bottom-range/attachment/sp-target-zone-3/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7560" title="S&amp;P Target Zone" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/SP-Target-Zone2-300x171.png" alt="" width="300" height="171" /></a></p>
<p>Volatility is still key and the big players (institutions) are leaving their mark.  Today the advance decline volume was a near 90% up day.  That bodes well for the short term.</p>
<p>Keep an eye on the price and volume bars.  That twosome will tell you more about the market&#8217;s disposition than any indicator I&#8217;ve ever seen.</p>
<p><span id="more-7559"></span>This hair-raising market slide may be over for the near term.  Don&#8217;t be fooled.  There will be more downside, but maybe not until price retraces some of this decline.</p>
<p>Wild intraday swings can still be brutal.  Yet the overlapping bars near a critical retracement level argue for a bit of stability.</p>
<p>Could this chart be showing short term capitulation volume?  It wouldn&#8217;t be a surprise to see the indexes try and retake their 200d moving averages.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7561" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/range-trading-2/bottom-range/attachment/nasdaq-54/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7561" title="NASDAQ" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/NASDAQ1-300x168.png" alt="" width="300" height="168" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7562" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/range-trading-2/bottom-range/attachment/sp-182/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7562" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/SP12-300x166.png" alt="" width="300" height="166" /></a></p>
<p>Today&#8217;s volume strength at near 90% and the attempt to stabilize near  the 38.2 with overlapping bars gives me a bit of confidence.</p>
<p>I&#8217;ve posted a few long ideas that I&#8217;m going to trade with only a wee bit of cash.</p>
<p><a href="http://tinyurl.com/4d3tfoc">Trade Sheet</a></p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/bottom-range/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
