      <description><![CDATA[No follow through with the stock market today.  The smartest place to be without question is in cash. This is the kind of market that will shred a portfolio.  Buying the impressive relief rallies is fine if you make a &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/ramblings-stock-market-today/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<h1>No follow through with the stock market today.  The smartest place to be without question is in cash.</h1>
<p>This is the kind of market that will shred a portfolio.  Buying the impressive relief rallies is fine if you make a quick exit.  Holding a long position before confirming a trend change is suicidal.  Just look at yesterday&#8217;s action and today&#8217;s market.</p>
<h2>As Treasuries climb they forecast that the global slowdown is here.  Watch in the coming months for the wizards of smart to say another recession or double dip began in the summer of &#8217;11.</h2>
<p>In the meantime, I&#8217;m focused on the shaded area on the following chart.  Within the shading is the 38.2 retracement zone.  Price touched that level earlier this week.  There may be some sloppy, choppy trading around the 38.2 level if price  tries to builds a ledge near it.</p>
<p>One day at a time . . .</p>
