      <title>The Bull Is Dead</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/bull-dead/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/bull-dead/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Wed, 10 Aug 2011 02:30:05 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Trading The Market]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[bear market]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[bull market]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[technical trading]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7529</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[photo credit: andrewmurray The bull market ended in May 2011 at the 1360ish high.  It looked like a potential for another push up was possible, but not now.  Technically, this market has violated all the levels that had to be &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/bull-dead/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><a title="Weird Replica Wall St bull" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/16581456@N00/5068866918/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4128/5068866918_4d48ed1f87_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Weird Replica Wall St bull" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution-NoDerivs License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="andrewmurray" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/16581456@N00/5068866918/" target="_blank">andrewmurray</a></small></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">The bull market ended in May 2011 at the 1360ish high.  It looked like a potential for another push up was possible, but not now.  Technically, this market has violated all the levels that had to be held and defended.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Expect the market to trade within this band for awhile.  This is a fairly strong ledge of support.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7531" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/bull-dead/attachment/sp-target-zone/"></a><a rel="attachment wp-att-7532" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/bull-dead/attachment/sp-target-zone-2/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7532" title="S&amp;P Target Zone" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/SP-Target-Zone1-300x171.png" alt="" width="300" height="171" /></a><br />
Relief rallies in a fear driven market can be impressive.  Don&#8217;t be fooled, be cautious.</p>
<p>This is not a fundamentally driven market.  The great earnings reports are forgotten among the rubble of this decline.</p>
<p>Three technical aspects are driving this market: hedge fund selling, margin calls, and mutual fund liquidation.  And lets not forget to add in the problems in Europe.</p>
<p>Will France be the next to receive a downgrade?  How willing do you think Germany will be to prop up another nation&#8217;s debt?  As I mentioned <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/stock-market-today/baby-bath-water/">here</a>, we are not alone in this most serious of economic debacles.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span id="more-7529"></span>The VIX hit 48 yesterday.  An extreme by all measures.</p>
<p>The Bullish Percent Index of the New York Composite is now trading beneath the March 2010 lows.  Expect a turn, but don&#8217;t expect it to last.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7530" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/bull-dead/attachment/nya/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7530" title="NYA" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/NYA-300x271.png" alt="" width="300" height="271" /></a></p>
<p>Let&#8217;s see if tomorrow offers any follow through.  If it kindles some novice traders&#8217; animal spirits to go long then it may be time to place a short trade or two.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/bull-dead/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>The Comfort Of Cash!</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/comfort-cash/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/comfort-cash/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Tue, 09 Aug 2011 02:07:50 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[cash]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7522</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Another staggering day of high volume selling.  This market is repricing for a global economic slowdown.  The collapse of bond yields point to that. A relief rally is somewhere on the horizon.  Scalp for a quick move if you must &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/comfort-cash/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Another staggering day of high volume selling.  This market is repricing for a global economic slowdown.  The collapse of bond yields point to that.</p>
<p>A relief rally is somewhere on the horizon.  Scalp for a quick move if you must because the pros will eventually sell any rally.</p>
<p>This is a renter&#8217;s not a buyer&#8217;s market.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7524" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/current-market-news/comfort-cash/attachment/sp-178/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7524" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/SP8-300x229.png" alt="" width="300" height="229" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span id="more-7522"></span>If a global slowdown is in the cards the worst is yet to come.  Lowered earnings, weak industrial production, and downward revised GDP numbers will be posted.  The ballooning unemployment numbers will only work to hammer stock prices in the days, weeks, and months to come, too.</p>
<p>Price sliced through the 61.8% retracement level like a hot knife through butter.  It is well within reason to think the entire move from July 2010 will be retraced.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/comfort-cash/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
