    <item>
      <title>Charts, Data, Analysis For The Week Beginning August 8th</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-8th/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-8th/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sat, 06 Aug 2011 17:07:28 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Charts, Data, Analysis]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[market analysis]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[stock charts]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[stock data]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7510</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Panics occurred both up and down this week showing that volatility makes for strange and risking trading days.  It looks like bounces should be sold. Watch the interaction of price and volume for clues that the market may stabilize.  We&#8217;re &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-8th/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Panics occurred both up and down this week showing that volatility makes for strange and risking trading days.  It looks like bounces should be sold.</p>
<p>Watch the interaction of price and volume for clues that the market may stabilize.  We&#8217;re not there yet.</p>
<p>Despite the volatility it&#8217;s critical to know where the range lines reside marking support and resistance.  Watch how price acts around those levels for hints of strength or weakness.</p>
<p>The S&amp;P 500 has sliced through 5 levels of support.  The 1170 level was broken intraday, but price closed above it.  If price closes below the 1170 level the next stop is 1125.</p>
<p>Very heavy selling on Friday.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7511" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-8th/attachment/sp-175/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7511" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/SP5-300x232.png" alt="" width="300" height="232" /></a></p>
<p>The DJ30 showed heavy buying on Friday.  Watch for follow through on Monday.  The DJ couldn&#8217;t hold 11690.  If there isn&#8217;t follow through then the next level to watch is 10,979.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7512" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-8th/attachment/sp-176/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7512" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/SP6-300x232.png" alt="" width="300" height="232" /></a></p>
<p>NASDAQ sliced through 2507 and nearly touched the next critical level at 2453.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7513" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-8th/attachment/nasdaq-53/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7513" title="NASDAQ" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/NASDAQ-300x233.png" alt="" width="300" height="233" /></a></p>
<p>A very interesting week ahead.  These are the times that a trader must have a plan and use it &#8212; check it before you wreck it in this market.</p>
<p><span id="more-7510"></span>It&#8217;s possible that the market drops further from here, but mathematically it&#8217;s not highly probable.  With that being said the risk does not warrant placing short or long trades.</p>
<p>Friday the S&amp;P discounted the US credit rating for the first time in history.  Anyone that pays attention must have known in their heart-of-hearts that this was going to happen.  The US debt is too great and there is no plan to stem the bleeding.</p>
<p>As traders, not crap shooters, we must think this through.</p>
<p>The Fed did respond to the downgrade in a press release, <a href="http://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/press/bcreg/20110805a.htm">HERE.</a> The FOMC meeting is Tuesday.  Could the downgrade be used as an excuse to launch QE3?  The ECB announced earlier in the week that it would support the bond markets in Italy and Spain.</p>
<p>If QE3 is announced watch the market&#8217;s reaction.</p>
<p><strong>Sector Action</strong></p>
<p>Here&#8217;s how bad the week was as bench marked against the S&amp;P &#8212; down -7.1%,</p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Metals  -12.2%</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Oil and Gas Exploration/Production 11.9</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Energy 10.1</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Materials  9.5</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Retail  9.0</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Industrials  8.4</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Discretionary  8.2</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Financials  7.5</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">HealthCare  7.4</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Technology  5.1</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Utilities  4.6</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Staples  4.3</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong><span style="color: #000000;">Statistical Scans</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;"><span style="color: #000000;">Nothing for the week.</span></span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;"><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Bottom Line:</strong></span></span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;"><span style="color: #000000;">Watch the market&#8217;s reaction to the news.  Monday&#8217;s action will be telling given the Friday downgrade by the S&amp;P rating agency.  Watch what the FOMC does, too.<br />
</span></span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;"><span style="color: #000000;">If the market continues to decline it may be the start of a correction that will remedy the up move started in 2009.  If that&#8217;s the case, much lower prices are ahead. </span></span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;"><span style="color: #000000;">The major indexes have been below the 50% retracement of the move from July 2010 to the highs made either in March or July depending on the index.  All have closed above that level.  Will the 50% retracement level retest before moving higher?</span></span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;"><span style="color: #000000;">Markets tend to overshoot levels to the upside and the downside.<br />
</span></span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;"><span style="color: #000000;">Lots of unanswered questions.  Most will find answers in the coming weeks.</span></span></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;"><span style="color: #000000;">Enjoy the weekend.  We&#8217;ll get back in the market when there are fewer bears and sharks.<br />
</span></span></p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-8th/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
