      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/ugly/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Fri, 05 Aug 2011 03:40:04 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7495</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[The market had been teflon-coated most of the year, but how things have changed! Finally, Wall Street can&#8217;t deny the damage and  is responding to the genius fiscal policies from Washington D.C.  Not since  1978 during the Jimmy Peanut Carter &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/ugly/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The market had been teflon-coated most of the year, but how things have changed!</p>
<p>Finally, Wall Street can&#8217;t deny the damage and  is responding to the genius fiscal policies from Washington D.C.  Not since  1978 during the Jimmy Peanut Carter presidency has the market had a series of  nine consecutive down days.</p>
<p>Expect more rosy news tomorrow when the employment numbers are released.</p>
<p>The US dollar became a safe haven, today.  This was the fear trade.  The trend line connecting lows from 2008 may be challenged.  That would take the dollar up toward the $78.00 level.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7496" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/current-market-news/ugly/attachment/dollar-40/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7496" title="Dollar" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Dollar-300x156.png" alt="" width="300" height="156" /></a></p>
<p>Treasuries were bought in droves, too.  Definitely a flight to safety.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7497" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/current-market-news/ugly/attachment/treasuries/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7497" title="Treasuries" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Treasuries-300x157.png" alt="" width="300" height="157" /></a></p>
<p>GLD has ended trading at the bottom of its range for the last two days, but it&#8217;s up for the week.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7498" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/current-market-news/ugly/attachment/gld-25/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7498" title="GLD" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/GLD-300x157.png" alt="" width="300" height="157" /></a></p>
<p>So where are we?</p>
<p>Well off the top, obviously, but maybe not yet at a bottom.  The red line is the &#8220;overbought&#8221; zone on this percent of stocks above the 200d MA chart.  The green line may be where the market is headed after slicing through the recent range lines of support (yellow lines).</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7503" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/current-market-news/ugly/attachment/200d-stocks-2/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7503" title="200d stocks" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/200d-stocks-300x150.png" alt="" width="300" height="150" /></a></p>
<p>Watch the futures and the overseas market for clues.  It could get even uglier.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/ugly/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>The Baby Went Out With The Bath Water!</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/baby-bath-water/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/baby-bath-water/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Thu, 04 Aug 2011 18:25:53 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7488</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[photo credit: jdsmith1021 &#160; It&#8217;s looking rough again today with more intense selling. Here are the negatives from the technical side: Breach of the 200d MA Price trading below the March lows Wednesday was a 90% down day Thursday is &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/baby-bath-water/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><a title="Bathing Baby Duck with Soap" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/25251003@N07/5809763439/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2655/5809763439_2d6ca7cfc2_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Bathing Baby Duck with Soap" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution-ShareAlike License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="jdsmith1021" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/25251003@N07/5809763439/" target="_blank">jdsmith1021</a></small></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">It&#8217;s looking rough again today with more intense selling.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Here are the negatives from the technical side:</p>
<p style="text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;">Breach of the 200d MA</p>
<p style="text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;">Price trading below the March lows</p>
<p style="text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;">Wednesday was a 90% down day</p>
<p style="text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;">Thursday is shaping up to be another 90% downer</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">All of the algorithms have kicked in and are creating the waterfall effect.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7489" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/stock-market-today/baby-bath-water/attachment/sp-174/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7489" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/SP4-300x175.png" alt="" width="300" height="175" /></a></p>
<p>Nobody is talking about this one &#8212; the Shangai Index is stalled.  Why is that so if everything economic is so great in China?</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7490" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/stock-market-today/baby-bath-water/attachment/shanghai/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7490" title="Shanghai" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Shanghai-300x177.png" alt="" width="300" height="177" /></a></p>
<p>Another bad sign has been the number of corporate layoffs.  This is big business protecting itself from the onslaught.</p>
<p>Protect your cash however you can.  This is ugly and looks global, not just a U.S. market meltdown.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
