      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>A new low was printed at 1235 before the market turned and moved higher.  Lots of overhead resistance looms if price tries to climb.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7480" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/current-market-news/wild-wednesday/attachment/sp-173/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7480" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/SP3-300x176.png" alt="" width="300" height="176" /></a></p>
<p>Today&#8217;s bar is resting against the underside of the median line and is well below the 200d MA.</p>
<p>The NDX accomplished a throw over (falling below the 200d MA, but closing above) and touched the median line.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7481" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/current-market-news/wild-wednesday/attachment/ndx-13/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7481" title="NDX" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/NDX2-300x178.png" alt="" width="300" height="178" /></a></p>
<p>Both indexes closed at the top of their bar&#8217;s range and on good volume.  It could be classified as an effort to rise pattern.  The next few days will be crucial.  Watch for a test bar.  That may be a good clue to take a trade.</p>
<p>Keep a keen eye on the watch lists as I&#8217;m suspecting a few signals may fire later this week or early next.</p>
<p><span id="more-7479"></span>I&#8217;m looking for short signals.  Those stocks that fell in sympathy with the S&amp;P may make the best candidates.  I&#8217;ll post the list as it develops.</p>
<p>GPOR was the last to fall, but it put up a mighty fight.  Let&#8217;s see if there is follow through tomorrow.</p>
