      <pubDate>Wed, 03 Aug 2011 03:59:47 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7461</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[&#8220;These are the times that try men&#8217;s souls.&#8221; &#8212; Thomas Paine It has certainly been tough to watch this shameful spectacle performed by the clowns in D.C.  I don&#8217;t know who&#8217;s fooled by it.  Certainly not the market. Expect more &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/stock-market-today-pt-ii/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>&#8220;These are the times that try men&#8217;s<em> </em>souls.&#8221; &#8212; Thomas Paine</p>
<p>It has certainly been tough to watch this shameful spectacle performed by the clowns in D.C.  I don&#8217;t know who&#8217;s fooled by it.  Certainly not the market.</p>
<p>Expect more of the same from the market and the D.C. clownfest.</p>
<p>This hourly chart shows the very weak S&amp;P about 20 minutes before the close.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7462" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/stock-market-today/stock-market-today-pt-ii/attachment/sp-172/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7462" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/SP2-300x142.png" alt="" width="300" height="142" /></a></p>
<p>This daily chart shows the outcome.  The close fell below the 1258 level and outside of the lower rail of the fork.  The next level to watch is the March low.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7463" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/stock-market-today/stock-market-today-pt-ii/attachment/spii-3/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7463" title="S&amp;PII" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/SPII-300x179.png" alt="" width="300" height="179" /></a></p>
<p>The DJ-30 looks bad, too, but not quite as bad as the S&amp;P.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7464" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/stock-market-today/stock-market-today-pt-ii/attachment/dj30-7/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7464" title="DJ30" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/DJ30-300x176.png" alt="" width="300" height="176" /></a></p>
<p>The NDX hasn&#8217;t reached the levels of either the S&amp;P or DJ-30.  A few more days like today and the NDX will be down there, too.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7465" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/stock-market-today/stock-market-today-pt-ii/attachment/ndx-11/"></a><a rel="attachment wp-att-7466" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/stock-market-today/stock-market-today-pt-ii/attachment/ndx-12/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7466" title="NDX" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/NDX1-300x168.png" alt="" width="300" height="168" /></a><br />
Technically speaking here&#8217;s what I&#8217;ll be watching to gauge a potential turn.  This technique is priceless.  Thank me later.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">In a downtrend watch the weakest of the major indices.  In an uptrend watch the strongest.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Gauge sentiment.  This current market is falling on every piece of bad news.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Know where the major support and resistance zones live.  You do this by studying at least two years worth of price data.  Weekly or daily it doesn&#8217;t matter.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Here&#8217;s the payoff:  when price closes in on a major support/resistance zone and sentiment turns, pay attention.  The top/bottom may be close at hand.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">This is what I mean: in a falling market when every piece of bad news sinks the tape be alert to when the market starts to shrug off the bad news.  Conversely in a rising market when the sentiment is rosy and everyone is happy beware when good news fails to lift the market higher.</p>
<p>The market always has lessons to teach and this market is being an especially harsh taskmaster.</p>
<p><span id="more-7461"></span></p>
<p>A crisis of confidence exists on Wall Street.  Bottom fishers beware.  Everything the market has ignored for the last few years is  now weighing heavily on its shoulders.</p>
<p>The market has to stop the drop before we can look for signals.  It hasn&#8217;t happened.  There have been 7 or 8 90% down days and only 1 to the upside.  Maybe another one will occur and clean out the sellers.</p>
<p>At the risk of sounding like a broken record, this market will have a tough time making headway given the time of year and the historical backdrop.  Best to be cautious, very cautious.</p>
<p>Bless that GPOR position.  It keeps on fighting and hasn&#8217;t been stopped.</p>
<p>Tomorrow&#8217;s another day.  Stay tuned for more nonsense.</p>
<p><a href="http://tinyurl.com/4d3tfoc">Trade Sheet</a></p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
