      <title>Pulling Strings</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/bad-worse/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/bad-worse/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Tue, 02 Aug 2011 04:14:24 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[stock market analysis]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7441</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[photo credit: David Noah1 The Geppetto&#8217;s in D.C. pulled the strings this morning.  They knew it had to be done before the Asian markets opened.  Consequently, the market made a big run to the upside after the debt deal was &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/bad-worse/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><a title="San Telmo Puppet" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/40883475@N00/5881029004/" target="_blank"><br />
</a><a title="_DSC5987.jpg" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/42384834@N07/5991964781/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://farm7.static.flickr.com/6141/5991964781_353de862ff_m.jpg" border="0" alt="_DSC5987.jpg" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="David Noah1" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/42384834@N07/5991964781/" target="_blank">David Noah1</a></small></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">
The Geppetto&#8217;s in D.C. pulled the strings this morning.  They knew it had to be done before the Asian markets opened.  Consequently, the market made a big run to the upside after the debt deal was announced.</p>
<p>Thud!  Down it came.  The smart guys knew that fading that market open was the right move and they were correct.</p>
<p>Kicking the can down the road only works for so long.  It looks like we&#8217;ve run out of road and the market players know it.</p>
<p>The S&amp;P traded below the 200dMA for a while this Monday.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7442" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/current-market-news/bad-worse/attachment/sp-170/"><img class="size-medium wp-image-7442 aligncenter" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/SP-300x179.png" alt="" width="300" height="179" /></a></p>
<p>The NASDAQ Composite hasn&#8217;t been below the critical 200d MA, but it may be headed there because . . .</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7444" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/current-market-news/bad-worse/attachment/comp-9/"><img class="size-medium wp-image-7444 aligncenter" title="COMP" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/COMP1-300x180.png" alt="" width="300" height="180" /></a></p>
<p>the Russell 2000 is there and closed below it.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7445" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/current-market-news/bad-worse/attachment/rut-31/"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7445" title="RUT" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/RUT-300x173.png" alt="" width="300" height="173" /></a><span id="more-7441"></span>We&#8217;ll have to cool our heels until the tape stabilizes.  I&#8217;m prepared to go either short or long, but I need a clear signal.</p>
<p>The RSI (14) sliced through the all important 50 mark heading south.  I&#8217;m expecting to see it in low double digits before any turnaround occurs.</p>
<p>One position left &#8212; GPOR.  HLX was stopped for another profit but it just couldn&#8217;t withstand the negative tape.</p>
<p>Another Monday in the books as is the first day of a new month.  Let&#8217;s see if the first few days of August will be positive as customary or if they continue to feed the slide.</p>
<p><a href="http://tinyurl.com/4d3tfoc">Trade Sheet.</a></p>
]]></content:encoded>
