      <category><![CDATA[Charts, Data, Analysis]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[stock charts]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[stock market analysis]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[stock market data]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7430</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Market commentary is useless until the political wrangling ends.  Some sort of resolution will likely occur this week.  Then we will be able to access the status of the market and the Founding Fathers will temporarily stop spinning in their &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-1st/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Market commentary is useless until the political wrangling ends.  Some sort of resolution will likely occur this week.  Then we will be able to access the status of the market and the Founding Fathers will temporarily stop spinning in their graves.</p>
<p>This chart shows bars  annotated with significant price and volume criteria and horizontal range lines of support and resistance.  Friday&#8217;s close broke a very significant cluster of range line support zones.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7431" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-1st/attachment/sp-169/"><img class="size-medium wp-image-7431 aligncenter" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/SP10-300x250.png" alt="" width="300" height="250" /></a></p>
<p>The VIX shot above the top Keltner band on Wednesday and never looked back.  It can go higher, but history argues for some sort of retracement back inside the bands.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7432" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-1st/attachment/vix-19/"><img class="size-medium wp-image-7432 aligncenter" title="VIX" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/VIX2-300x227.png" alt="" width="300" height="227" /></a></p>
<p>The number of stocks trading above the 200d MA is approaching a prior turning point.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7433" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-august-1st/attachment/200d-stocks/"><img class="size-medium wp-image-7433 aligncenter" title="200d stocks" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/200d-stocks-300x229.png" alt="" width="300" height="229" /></a></p>
<p>Hopefully, everyone has been using stops and obeying them.  This has been a dreadful week not only for the market, but for the health and status of our country, too.</p>
<p><span id="more-7430"></span><strong>Sector Analysis</strong></p>
<p>The S&amp;P got whacked -3.3% .  The sectors look like this for the week:</p>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Utilities  -0.9</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Staples  2.2</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Technology  2.6</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Consumer Discretionary  3.0</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Retail  3.0</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Financial  3.1</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Energy  3.1</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">HealthCare  3.6</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Materials  3.7</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Oil and Gas Exploration/Production  4.3</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Industrials  5.3</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Metals and Mining  6.6</span></address>
<address> </address>
<p><strong>Statistical Scans</strong></p>
<p>None of the statistical scans provided credible candidates for a long trade.  This is one of those times when it&#8217;s best to sit on our hands and wait for set-ups and signals.</p>
<p><strong>Bottom Line:</strong></p>
<p>Here we go again.  This lousy tape reminds me of the one from early June.  It was a free fall down into the middle of the month and then some chop.  We&#8217;ll have to wait and see if the drop has ended before worrying about choppy trading this time around.</p>
<p>Most of the trades on the Trade Sheet were stopped, but many were stopped with profits.</p>
<p>GPOR took off again on Friday and has eclipsed a short term resistance zone.  The stop has been raised on this one.</p>
<p>HLX looked a little weak after the big move up on July 26th.  Thursday&#8217;s action was a bit concerning as price closed near the bottom of the day&#8217;s range and formed a dragonfly bar after the prior false up thrust.  Friday the stock closed a bit above the open, but well off the highs.  We&#8217;ll just have to keep an eye and the stop on this one.</p>
<p>TSO got stopped for a minor loss.  Unless this one breaks the prior low made on July 14th I&#8217;m keeping it on my radar.</p>
<p>Keep the faith and know that again money was banked on this batch of trades.  I&#8217;ll be watching for long or short opportunities and you&#8217;ll be the first to know when I find them.</p>
<p>Have a relaxing weekend.</p>
<p><a href="http://tinyurl.com/4d3tfoc">Trade Sheet</a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
