<p>Day two of the gap down opening.  Price moved below the 50d MA and proceeded to slice through the 150d MA like it wasn&#8217;t even there.</p>
<p>The debt ceiling talks are weighing on the market as are the lousy Beige Book numbers and the crummy durable goods data.  It all points to an economy that is wheezing.</p>
<p>Good earnings reports from Amazon, Whole Foods, and Boeing. Those reports are quickly soured by forward looking statements that are not encouraging.</p>
<p>My best advice &#8212; keep your cash safely tucked inside the Mason jar.</p>
<p><span id="more-7419"></span></p>
<p>Not much more to say about this market.  Stops took out a couple of positions; stops will keep the profits safe.</p>
<p>There&#8217;s a bounce out there somewhere.  It may be a good shorting opportunity.  We&#8217;ll know more when we see it.</p>
