      <description><![CDATA[Until there is a resolution to the debt ceiling issue the Washington D.C. wrangling will affect the market&#8217;s behavior.  I&#8217;m not planning new positions until the dust settles and the smoke clears. This is a very dangerous game being played &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/spectacle-affecting-market/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Until there is a resolution to the debt ceiling issue the Washington D.C. wrangling will affect the market&#8217;s behavior.  I&#8217;m not planning new positions until the dust settles and the smoke clears.</p>
<p>This is a very dangerous game being played in D.C.  Will it take a market plunge to wake up the lawmakers?  I hope not.</p>
<p><span id="more-7394"></span></p>
<p>Random Thoughts For Monday Night:</p>
<p>The market held up well.  I liked the way stocks traded especially the TSO position.</p>
<p>With so much headline risk I&#8217;m finding few stocks setting up or signalling.</p>
<p>I want the S&amp;P to break this high.  If it doesn&#8217;t then expect more sideways grinding.</p>
<p>The NASDAQ 100 broke to new highs on Friday and came in a bit today, but ended higher.  If the NDX can hang out at these high levels it gives me hope that when the debt dance ends we may move higher.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7396" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/current-market-news/spectacle-affecting-market/attachment/sp-167/"><img class="size-medium wp-image-7396 aligncenter" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/SP8-300x179.png" alt="" width="300" height="179" /></a></p>
