      <description><![CDATA[Yesterday&#8217;s tape was revealing and today provided the follow-through I&#8217;d hoped we&#8217;d see.  Last night I wrote to members that the lack of supply (sellers waiting to unload) looked like a bullish sign.  Tonight finds price at the top of &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/nice-upside-effort/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Yesterday&#8217;s tape was revealing and today provided the follow-through I&#8217;d hoped we&#8217;d see.  Last night <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/crawl-continue/">I wrote</a> to members that the lack of supply (sellers waiting to unload) looked like a bullish sign.  Tonight finds price at the top of the range on very nice volume.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7378" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/range-trading-2/nice-upside-effort/attachment/spd-4/"><img class="size-medium wp-image-7378 aligncenter" title="S&amp;Pd" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/SPd3-300x296.png" alt="" width="300" height="296" /></a></p>
<p>The market needs to get past <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/stock-market-today/stock-market-today-levels-watch/">these range resistance levels</a> to prove that its bullish swagger has returned.</p>
<p><span id="more-7377"></span>The move up on higher volume is hopeful, but we need to keep our eyes open for trouble.  Do you realize that the market has been trading sideways since February?</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7379" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/range-trading-2/nice-upside-effort/attachment/sp-165/"><img class="size-medium wp-image-7379 aligncenter" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/SP6-300x194.png" alt="" width="300" height="194" /></a></p>
<p>Let&#8217;s go into the weekend playing the hand we&#8217;ve dealt.  Price is getting close to old highs.  Now is not the time to pile on new trades.</p>
<p>If the market breaks to new highs that should be a very bullish signal.  The first pullback from new highs will be the time to strike.</p>
<p>Updated stops are on the<a href="http://tinyurl.com/4d3tfoc"> Trade Sheet.</a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
