      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7372</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[This is a &#8220;prove it&#8221; kind of tape. Today&#8217;s trading provided another higher low.  The bulls must keep the crawl going while the bears lick their chops hoping for the slightest misstep. Good news tonight on the earnings front from &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/crawl-continue/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>This is a &#8220;prove it&#8221; kind of tape.</p>
<p>Today&#8217;s trading provided another higher low.  The bulls must keep the crawl going while the bears lick their chops hoping for the slightest misstep.</p>
<p><span id="more-7372"></span></p>
<p>Good news tonight on the earnings front from Intel.  Watch tomorrow&#8217;s reaction.</p>
<p>Apple&#8217;s blowout numbers fueled a big push, but tonight I see that the mighty one closed at the bottom of its range.  This type of action is a bit worrisome because it seems like an attempt to lock long traders into a tough position.</p>
<p>1295 looks like good short term support on the S&amp;P.  There was a test of supply (sellers waiting to unload)  and there were none.  A very good sign, but there are two  more trading days in this week.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s best to wait for confirmation of strength before adding many more positions.</p>
<p>Stay on your toes and keep those stops in place.</p>
