      <description><![CDATA[photo credit: esharkj Trading today&#8217;s market was fun if you were long. The tape turned on the AAPL news and the rest of tech land and the market followed.  For the market to make serious headway north it needs to &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/panic-mode-hallelujah/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><a title="iPad Wallpaper | Pop Retro" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/89889506@N00/5949122439/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://farm7.static.flickr.com/6137/5949122439_e22b9bfaac_m.jpg" border="0" alt="iPad Wallpaper | Pop Retro" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="esharkj" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/89889506@N00/5949122439/" target="_blank">esharkj</a></small></p>
<p>Trading today&#8217;s market was fun if you were long.</p>
<p>The tape turned on the AAPL news and the rest of tech land and the market followed.  For the market to make serious headway north it needs to surpass three stiff range trading resistance zones: 1344, 1356, and then 1370.  If it can&#8217;t work its way beyond these levels then it looks like a sideways grind that will chew on both long and short traders.</p>
<p>Support held at 1294.  Despite today&#8217;s nice lift it was on below average volume.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s still a tough tape.  If you&#8217;re inclined to trade these smaller swings here&#8217;s a suggestion.  Find exceptional profit opportunities and set a profit target (either a percentage or a dollar amount).  Sell a portion of the position  and take the money at the first profit target.  Keep a stop on the remaining shares and sell them when the stop is hit.</p>
<p>Subscribers got a chance to trade GPOR and quickly bank some cash.  That stock is a good example of finding the opportunity and then taking partial profits ASAP!</p>
<p><span id="more-7362"></span></p>
<p>Today was another stellar day because GPOR hit its first profit target.  I suggest that as your buy orders fill place a sell order at the first profit target price.  Place a sell order at the stop price, too.  Bracketing the purchase price with a sell order at the profit target and one at the stop price saves time and kills the emotions of fear and greed.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m hoping we see a push to higher levels like we did in late June.  That move was very impulsive and fast.</p>
<p>The <a href="http://tinyurl.com/4d3tfoc">Trade Sheet </a>has a couple of new ideas for tomorrow.  I have my fingers, toes, and eyes crossed for luck and another good trading day!</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
