      <title>Charts, Data, Analysis For The Week Beginning July 18th</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-july-18th/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-july-18th/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sat, 16 Jul 2011 16:57:58 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Charts, Data, Analysis]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[market analysis]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[stock and market data]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[stock charts]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7344</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[This is a tape that is holding support in spite of bad news.  Economic news was front and center all week replete with bickering and dire forecasts.  The market held itself together and failed to deepen its slide. In this &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-july-18th/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>This is a tape that is holding support in spite of bad news.  Economic news was front and center all week replete with bickering and dire forecasts.  The market held itself together and failed to deepen its slide.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/trading-focus/">In this post,</a> I remarked to members that 1311 looked like an area of range trading support.  Sure enough, this hourly chart of the S&amp;P shows price dancing back and forth across the 200h MA very near 1311.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-7345" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-july-18th/attachment/sph-3/"><img class="size-medium wp-image-7345 aligncenter" title="S&amp;Ph" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/SPh2-300x235.png" alt="Range Trading" width="300" height="235" /></a></p>
<p>If price can exceed the pivot high marked by the yellow arrow it may be starting a renewed push higher.</p>
<p>This daily chart of the S&amp;P looks encouraging, too.  The Friday&#8217;s big volume bar coupled with price closing near the high is a sign of strength.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7346" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-july-18th/attachment/spd-2/"><img class="size-medium wp-image-7346 aligncenter" title="S&amp;Pd" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/SPd1-300x267.png" alt="Range Trader" width="300" height="267" /></a></p>
<p>The  junior indexes touched the 50d MA and then leaped from it.  No doubt it was in reaction to Google&#8217;s absolute crush of their quarterly earnings.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7347" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-july-18th/attachment/nasdaq-50/"><img class="size-medium wp-image-7347 aligncenter" title="NASDAQ" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/NASDAQ2-300x180.png" alt="Range Lines" width="300" height="180" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Gold made headlines all week as it approached and exceeded old highs.  The miners are less flamboyant.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7348" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-july-18th/attachment/gld-24/"><img class="size-medium wp-image-7348 aligncenter" title="GLD" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/GLD-300x197.png" alt="" width="300" height="197" /></a></p>
<p>If the miners can take out the pivot high at $60 then the bullion may march higher.  The miners are often a good &#8220;tell&#8221; for the metal.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7349" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-july-18th/attachment/gdx-2/"><img class="size-medium wp-image-7349 aligncenter" title="GDX" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/GDX-300x208.png" alt="" width="300" height="208" /></a></p>
<p>Oil has a very intriguing chart.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7350" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-july-18th/attachment/xoi/"><img class="size-medium wp-image-7350 aligncenter" title="XOI" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/XOI-300x195.png" alt="" width="300" height="195" /></a></p>
<p>The US dollar keeps bumping along.  Notice that despite the grind that higher lows and higher highs are the pattern.  That long term trend line (yellow) is getting closer and will likely provide stiff resistance.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7351" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-beginning-july-18th/attachment/us-dollar-13/"><img class="size-medium wp-image-7351 aligncenter" title="US dollar" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/US-dollar-300x209.png" alt="" width="300" height="209" /></a></p>
<p>If you&#8217;re participating in the market with long trades don&#8217;t give up just yet.  It looks like this tape is willing to fight off all antagonists!</p>
<p>Caveat:  pick your plays carefully.</p>
<p><em>Beyond this point members receive more detailed analysis and focus.  We look at the best areas in the market to place fresh cash and we try to time our entries.  First profit targets are a hallmark of the Range Trader style.  It&#8217;s important to put some profits in the bank when they&#8217;re offered.  If interested, membership details are on the right sidebar.</em></p>
<p><span id="more-7344"></span></p>
<p><strong>Sector Analysis</strong></p>
<p>The S&amp;P was off 2.06% for the week.  The sectors fell in line as follows:</p>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Oil and Gas  +2.4%</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Energy  -.04</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Utilities  1.1</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Staples  1.2</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Materials  1.6</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">HealthCare  1.6</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Metals and Mining  1.8</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Technology  2.0</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Consumer Discretionary 2.6</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Retail  2.8</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Industrials  3.3</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Financials  3.9</span></address>
<address>
</address>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Statistical Scans:</strong></p>
<p><strong><em>2% Daily</em></strong> &#8212; If you like to try and capture a 2% gain per day these are the ones to watch.  Each of them has a daily range in excess of $1.00</p>
<p>JVA  BAS  CDE  TVIX  OAS  SPWRA  GPOR  HOGS  CPX</p>
<p><strong><em>3% Weekly</em></strong> &#8212; This list contains those stocks that reliably move 3% week over week.  They can be traded from a daily or weekly chart.  I&#8217;ve found it best to give them room to move by not setting stops too close and then taking profits as soon as the 3% gain is made.</p>
<p>BPI  CVI  DDS  GMCR  TIN  ULTA</p>
<p><strong><em>10% Weekly</em></strong> &#8211;  The gains are bigger, but the idea is the same as the 3% weekly.  This is a very exclusive list with consistent gains.</p>
<p>AGQ  ARIA  BAS  TZOO</p>
<p><em><strong>The Once A Week Trader </strong></em> &#8212; This is my old bread and butter method.  A good, solid strategy that rips and roars in an uptrend!</p>
<p>ARIA  BPI  MPEL  PAG  PCYC  SPWRA</p>
<p><strong>The Bottom Line:</strong></p>
<p>When the market is holding its own in the face of political bickering, dire economic forecasts, and devastating employment numbers it tells me that there&#8217;s a good chance it will climb higher.  The important thing to do is pick plays carefully.<strong><br />
</strong></p>
<p>The energy space looks good, especially oil and gas.  It was the one and only green giant sector for the past week.</p>
<p>The crack spreads are off the charts.  If you&#8217;re not familiar with that term it means the spread or profit the oil industry can make from the products extracted (cracked) from crude oil.  Think heating oil, jet fuel, gasoline, diesel, etc.</p>
<p>That tells me that the refiners should be making lots of money.  I have some names I&#8217;m watching, but they haven&#8217;t signaled &#8212; TSO, VLO, MRO</p>
<p>New ideas and fresh stops are on the trade sheet.  Hope you&#8217;re having a great weekend!</p>
<p><a href="http://tinyurl.com/4d3tfoc">Trade Sheet</a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
