      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Another range trading day on the major indexes.  Two days of sideways price action is the hallmark of a bull versus bear battle.  The 50d MA remains the ledge of support.  Until this market can close green the bears are going to feel feisty.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-7340" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/range-trading-2/range-trading-5/attachment/sp-164/"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-7340" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/SP5-300x200.png" alt="" width="300" height="200" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span id="more-7339"></span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Mid-session gains and a negative close is not going to turn this market.  Tomorrow is options expiration and nothing will seem real.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Maybe Google&#8217;s after hours earnings crush will lift tomorrow&#8217;s tape.  Watch the Friday close for clues.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Time for hand-sitting or thumb twiddling.  This too shall pass.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://tinyurl.com/4d3tfoc">Trade Sheet</a></p>
