    <item>
      <title>Trading The Market: Focus</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/trading-focus/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/trading-focus/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Tue, 12 Jul 2011 01:00:10 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Trading The Market]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7315</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[It was a negative day from the start.  In fact, it seemed to snowball on last Friday&#8217;s lousy employment number. Stay focused on the charts and not on the news. This daily chart of the S&#38;P 500 has two forks &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/trading-focus/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>It was a negative day from the start.  In fact, it seemed to snowball on last Friday&#8217;s lousy employment number.</p>
<p>Stay focused on the charts and not on the news.</p>
<p>This daily chart of the S&amp;P 500 has two forks that clearly encapsulate price.</p>
<p>Notice the longer term blue fork.  It was drawn from the lowest and highest pivot point during the sideways move from February to early May.  After breaking above the top blue rail, price has come back in and is resting on the top of the highest rail.  Bottom line &#8212; price has returned to its breakout point.</p>
<p>Nothing to worry about, yet.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7316" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/trading-focus/attachment/sp-163/"><img class="size-medium wp-image-7316 aligncenter" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/SP4-300x197.png" alt="" width="300" height="197" /></a></p>
<p><em>More detailed analysis and trading ideas follow for members.</em></p>
<p><span id="more-7315"></span>The yellow fork  was drawn from the first high after the June 16 low and the lowest low following the high (June 23rd).  The anchor for the median line is the June 16th low.  This very narrow up channel still contains price as seen on the first chart.</p>
<p>So far so good.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m thinking there may be a bit more downside.  Here&#8217;s why:  the move off the June 16 low looks like an impulsive first wave.  I&#8217;ve counted it in yellow on this hourly chart.  We may have  just completed the first wave to the upside in a fresh bull phase.  Now price is working on a corrective counter trend or wave 2.</p>
<p>According to the wave rules of alternation a corrective leg should be different from the prior corrective leg.  I think that&#8217;s what is on the chart&#8211;I can count three waves with the third wave still completing.  It is a five wave move where wave 4 of the up move was more a-b-c in appearance.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-7318" href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/trading-focus/attachment/sph-2/"><img class="size-medium wp-image-7318 aligncenter" title="S&amp;Ph" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/SPh1-300x235.png" alt="" width="300" height="235" /></a></p>
<p>If this wave count is close to being correct it may complete near the 200h MA on this hourly chart or near 1311.  Then I would expect a brief move up (wave 4) and then a retest of the 200h MA for wave 5.</p>
<p>This is all guesswork and what-may-happen prognostication.  But  If I&#8217;m correct, at the completion of wave 5 of counter wave 2, price should start to climb again.</p>
<p>The two caveats are these:  price should not fall into the area of wave 1 marked by the yellow arrow.</p>
<p>Secondly, we will know if wave 3 is likely underway when it exceeds the high of wave 1 at 1356.</p>
<p>In summary, I&#8217;m still optimistic about the track of the market.  I think the dismal news on the US economy and world financial conditions will give the market a big ol&#8217; wall of worry to climb.  I also think the market&#8217;s rise from the June lows was telegraphing news that the earnings season was going to be a good one.</p>
<p>Alcoa beat estimates tonight.  Maybe that will start the ball rolling.</p>
<p>So that&#8217;s the tone for the week.  Despite today&#8217;s bright red trading day little damage was done to current positions.</p>
<p>A couple of fresh ideas are on the <a href="http://tinyurl.com/4d3tfoc">Trade Sheet.</a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
