    <item>
      <title>Charts, Data, Analysis For The Week Of July 11th</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/charts-data-analysis-week-2/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/charts-data-analysis-week-2/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sat, 09 Jul 2011 21:56:39 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[range trader]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[range trading]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7295</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[It was a battle all week.  The Tuesday to Wednesday action was listless, but Thursday was explosive.  Friday gave back a few points, and closed off the lows. Range trader resistance lines kept price contained on most of the averages. &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/charts-data-analysis-week-2/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>It was a battle all week.  The Tuesday to Wednesday action was listless, but Thursday was explosive.  Friday gave back a few points, and closed off the lows.</p>
<h1>Range trader resistance lines kept price contained on most of the averages.</h1>
<h3>The S&amp;P 500 probed higher highs on Thursday, but gave some back on Friday.  The first range trader resistance line is 1383 and the second is 1460.  That&#8217;s quite a spread!</h3>
<p>Support can be found at 1332 and then at 1327.  Volume has been below average for the entire move off the June lows. Price is still contained within the top rail and median line of the pitchfork.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/SP3.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7296" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/SP3-300x174.png" alt="" width="300" height="174" /></a></p>
<p>The NASDAQ and NDX have performed a moonshot &#8212; straight up and looking very fragile.  The gap from Wednesday to Thursday is very bullish and it was accompanied by decent volume.  It looks like this move has has gone a bit too far, too fast.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/NASDAQ1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7297" title="NASDAQ" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/NASDAQ1-300x175.png" alt="" width="300" height="175" /></a></p>
<p>The US dollar has been caught in a sideways current.  It&#8217;s still below the long-term trend line connecting the 11/27/2009 and 11/12/2010 lows.</p>
<p>I also see that the greenback has made higher lows with a relatively flat top on this weekly chart &#8212; an expanding triangle, maybe?  This pattern is often seen at tops and bottoms.  It looks like the dollar is coiling and building strength.  Expect a move later this year?</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/US-Dollar1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7298" title="US Dollar" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/US-Dollar1-300x171.png" alt="" width="300" height="171" /></a></p>
<h2>The XOI has climbed off the lows and spent most of its time consolidating.  There&#8217;s an old range trader resistance line at 1340 that&#8217;s acting like a lid.  Yet I expect to find some trades signalling in this sector.</h2>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Oil2.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7300" title="Oil" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Oil2-300x176.png" alt="" width="300" height="176" /></a></p>
<p>The Gold/Silver index has moved about 10 points off the low.  It&#8217;s again encountering range resistance at 210.  Price is still caught in the larger bearish fork (blue).  Until it breaks above that upper rail I&#8217;m a bit cautious.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/GoldSilver.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7301" title="Gold~Silver" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/GoldSilver-300x223.png" alt="" width="300" height="223" /></a></p>
<p>Keep an eye on the range trader resistance lines.  Volume at those levels will be the tell if price can pop through them.</p>
<p><span id="more-7295"></span></p>
<p><strong>Sector Analysis</strong></p>
<p>The Bullish Percent numbers show a market that has certainly come off its lofty levels.  The numbers show a regression to the mean, not a market in trouble.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/BullPercents.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7302" title="BullPercents" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/BullPercents-300x191.png" alt="" width="300" height="191" /></a></p>
<p>For the week the S&amp;P gained 0.31%.  The sectors fell in line like this:</p>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Retail  +2.7%</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Oil and Gas  1.7</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Technology  1.3</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Materials  1.2</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Energy  1.0</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Consumer Staples 0.8</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Consumer Discretionary  0.8</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Metals and Mining  0.7</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Industrials  -0.2%</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Utilities  0.3</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Health Care  0.5</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Financial  1.0</span></address>
<address> </address>
<p><strong>Statistical Scans</strong></p>
<p>2% Daily</p>
<p>JVA  BAS  CPX  CVI  MPEL</p>
<p>3% Weekly</p>
<p>AVEO  BPI  COG  DDS  MNTA  REGN  SODA  TIN  ULTA</p>
<p>10% Weekly</p>
<p>AGQ  ARIA  BAS  TZOO</p>
<p>The Once A Week Trader</p>
<p>ARIA  AUQ    AVEO  BPI  CVI  JVA  KEG  LPSN  MPEL  NANO  PAG  PCYC  QCOR  SAPE  SCSS  SOLR</p>
<address> </address>
<p>This next week is jammed with economic reports and options expiration.  It could be a wild one!</p>
<p>I&#8217;ve updated some of the stops and found a few trading ideas for Monday morning.  They&#8217;re on the <a rel="nofollow" href="http://tiny.cc/fd9t3">Trade Sheet.</a></p>
<p>Enjoy the weekend &#8212; see you after Monday&#8217;s close.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<address> </address>
]]></content:encoded>
