      <category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7280</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[The market needs a breather.  Price has gone too far too fast and a pause to catch up is a good thing. Savvy traders that missed the move a week ago should be making a list.  Look for stocks that &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/good/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The market needs a breather.  Price has gone too far too fast and a pause to catch up is a good thing.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/SP.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7281" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/SP-300x177.png" alt="" width="300" height="177" /></a></p>
<p>Savvy traders that missed the move a week ago should be making a list.  Look for stocks that have run and are now stalling.  Those will likely make a move when this upswing restarts its push to higher levels.</p>
<p><span id="more-7280"></span>Today&#8217;s volume and range contraction are hallmark signs of a market that&#8217;s pausing.  It will work of these conditions by coming in a little or going sideways for a few days.</p>
<p>The Trade Sheet stocks are still holding their own and profits should have been banked on a couple positions today.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s not time to add new positions, but I have several stocks on a watchlist that have caught my attention.  When the conditions are right they should signal and off we go again on a climb to higher levels!</p>
<p><a href="http://tiny.cc/w841s">Trade Sheet</a></p>
