    <item>
      <title>Charts, Data, Analysis For The Week Of July 5th</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-july-5th/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-july-5th/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sat, 02 Jul 2011 20:29:28 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Charts, Data, Analysis]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Analysis]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[data]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Gold]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[S&P]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[US Dollar. Charts]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[vix]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7258</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[photo credit: TeresaH12 &#160; It was surprising to me to read how many big name traders missed last week&#8217;s big move.  And when I say &#8220;big name&#8221; I mean names-you-would- recognize- traders that were insisting all week that the short &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/charts-data-analysis/charts-data-analysis-week-july-5th/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center; padding-left: 30px;"><a title="US Flag - RED, WHITE &amp; BLUE" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/52909119@N07/5647384106/" target="_blank"rel="nofollow"><img src="http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5227/5647384106_d5f8232d70_m.jpg" border="0" alt="US Flag - RED, WHITE &amp; BLUE"rel="nofollow" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="TeresaH12" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/52909119@N07/5647384106/" target="_blank"rel="nofollow">TeresaH12</a></small></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">It was surprising to me to read how many big name traders missed last week&#8217;s big move.  And when I say &#8220;big name&#8221; I mean names-you-would- recognize- traders that were insisting all week that the short side was the right side to play.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Don&#8217;t fight the market with a preconceived idea about its direction, just go where the market goes.</p>
<h2 style="text-align: left;">Yes, there were clues that a lift was more than likely.  In last week&#8217;s<a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/current-market-news/charts-data-analysis-week-june-27th/"> Charts, Data, Analysis post</a> I mentioned this observation about the S&amp;P 500 &#8211;</h2>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">&#8220;Yet I looked at this chart and wondered if Friday was a washout day for  sellers?  The price bar has a large range from high to low and volume  was enormous compared to the last few days&#8221;</p>
<p>And in the member section &#8211;</p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">&#8220;As the broad market took a beating AAPL found its footing and leaped off an old support level.  This is a clue that should not be ignored. . .</p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Will price cross the pivot high and the 1300ish level?  I kind of think so, here’s why –</p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Clue #1  The way AAPL is acting is hopeful.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Clue #2  The Transports have already pierced the critical level and did it on big volume&#8221;.</p>
<p>Here&#8217;s a look at the charts:</p>
<p>The weekly S&amp;P has a very bullish look as price is above the top rail of the fork.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/SPw.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7259" title="S&amp;Pw" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/SPw-300x194.png" alt="" width="300" height="194" /></a></p>
<p>Ditto for the DJ-30, NASDAQ Composite, and NDX.</p>
<p>Oil looks like it may have some potential for upside on this weekly chart:</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Oil.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7260" title="Oil" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Oil-300x197.png" alt="" width="300" height="197" /></a></p>
<p>The Gold/Silver index still looks sloppy and corrective.  The lower highs and lower lows gives it away and it pays to be a bit cautious in the precious metals arena.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Gold-Silver.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7261" title="Gold Silver" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Gold-Silver-300x196.png" alt="" width="300" height="196" /></a></p>
<p>The U.S. dollar is making headway, but slowly.  It&#8217;s taking one step forward and one step backwards.  Until it can break above the yellow trend line expect more chop.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/US-Dollar.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7262" title="US Dollar" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/US-Dollar-300x196.png" alt="" width="300" height="196" /></a></p>
<p>Here&#8217;s a daily VIX chart looking very lazy and complacent.  Trading outside of the Keltner channel is akin to a visual pothole on this chart.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/VIX.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7263" title="VIX" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/VIX-300x245.png" alt="" width="300" height="245" /></a></p>
<p>Next week will be a short week and likely an interesting one.</p>
<h3>More Charts, Data, Analysis follows for my peeps!</h3>
<p><span id="more-7258"></span><strong>Sector Analysis</strong></p>
<p>For the week the S&amp;P gained 5.6%.  It was a green week for all of  the sectors and they fell in line as follows:</p>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Oil and Gas Exploration  8.2%</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Energy  7.2</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Metals and Mining  7</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Consumer Discretionary  6.5</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Technology  6.4</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Industrials  6.4</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Materials  6</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Financials  5.8</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Retail  4.7</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Health Care  3.6</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Utilities  3.2</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Staples  2.8</span></address>
<address> </address>
<p><strong>Statistical Scans</strong></p>
<p>2% Daily</p>
<p>AG, ARUN, BAS, BBVA, CVI, EDC, EXXI,FNSR, FTO, SPRD, TSL</p>
<p>3% Weekly</p>
<p>BAS, BEXP, COG, CVI, DDS, REGN, SODA, TIN, ULTA</p>
<p>10% Weekly</p>
<p>AGQ, ARIA, BAS,  BKS, FNSR, JVA, MAKO, PCYC, SOLR, TZOO</p>
<p>The Once A Week Trader</p>
<p>AH, ARIA, AVEO, BPI, CVI, ELN, FTNT, JVA, LPSN, MPEL, NANO, PAG, PCYC, QCOR, SAH, SAPE,</p>
<p>SCSS, SOLR</p>
<p><strong>The Bottom Line</strong></p>
<p>Before adding more positions to the current list I&#8217;m going to wait for a pullback.  This move is unsustainable at this rate of ascent.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/SPd.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7265" title="S&amp;Pd" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/SPd-300x177.png" alt="" width="300" height="177" /></a></p>
<p>Remember that VIX chart?  The most recent value is outside the Keltner bands and that may be a signal that a bit of a retreat is due.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/VIX1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7266" title="VIX" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/VIX1-300x245.png" alt="" width="300" height="245" /></a></p>
<p>Longer term, I think the summer rally is here and the market is telling us that earnings season is apt to be a good one.   The weekly charts have turned up and the weekly moving averages are now showing a northerly tilt.</p>
<p>In addition, the semiconductors and financials (SMH and XLF) are trading in tandem.  This is a strong sign that a fledgling trend is about to take flight. Unlike the big name traders, I&#8217;d be loathe to short the market when I see this combo on the same team.</p>
<p>A very impressive week to be sure &#8212; 74 S&amp;P points to the upside.</p>
<p>Happy Independence Day!  Have fun and be safe.</p>
