    <item>
      <title>Lore For Stock Traders And Investors</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/lore-stock-traders-investors/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/lore-stock-traders-investors/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Fri, 01 Jul 2011 00:48:53 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Trading The Market]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Elliot waves]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Fibonacci Levels]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Range Lines]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[range trading]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[traders and investors]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7243</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Most traders and investors fail to understand two important concepts: #1:  when the market has seemingly insurmountable obstacles (bad economy, dire financial headlines) it&#8217;s likely to rise. #2:  when the economic backdrop is rosy and the market is smokin&#8217; that&#8217;s &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/lore-stock-traders-investors/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<h1>Most traders and investors fail to understand two important concepts:</h1>
<p>#1:  when the market has seemingly insurmountable obstacles (bad economy, dire financial headlines) it&#8217;s likely to rise.</p>
<p>#2:  when the economic backdrop is rosy and the market is smokin&#8217; that&#8217;s when it&#8217;s ripe for a fall.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s safe to say we&#8217;re experiencing condition #1.  Economically, things couldn&#8217;t look much worse for the U.S. or the world&#8217;s financial systems.</p>
<p>Today marked the fourth straight day of gains.  The S&amp;P 500 is well above the pivot high of 1298 and climbing higher in a very narrow channel.</p>
<h2>Stock traders and investors with a membership have seen trade ideas and are currently riding this upswing.</h2>
<p>Premium content beyond this point.  Registration information is available on the sidebar.</p>
<p><span id="more-7243"></span>The following chart is representative of many of the index charts.  The blue line is a linear regression line, the green line is a trend line, and the dashed white lines is a pitchfork.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/SP7.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7244" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/SP7-300x223.png" alt="" width="300" height="223" /></a></p>
<p>By any measure the downtrend has been broken.  I&#8217;m going to venture out on a limb and say the lows were in at the 200 d MA.  This chart shows the median line holding price above the 200 with only one brief venture below it on June 16th.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/SP-fork.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7245" title="S&amp;P fork" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/SP-fork-300x197.png" alt="" width="300" height="197" /></a></p>
<p>Here&#8217;s what we need to watch &#8212; the 61.8% Fibonacci level.  This level will often times stop an up move, if only briefly.</p>
<p>The Fibonacci retracement measurement should be taken from the May 2nd high to the June 16th low.  This is how it looks on the S&amp;P &#8211;</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/SP-Fibs.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7246" title="S&amp;P Fibs" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/SP-Fibs-300x225.png" alt="" width="300" height="225" /></a></p>
<p>The 61.8% level is 1327.8.  Tonight&#8217;s close was 1320.54 &#8212; very close.  The nearest Range Resistance line is at 1339.  I&#8217;m showing these levels to make you aware.</p>
<p>Now for some good news.  I think the market <strong><em>may</em></strong> be headed much higher.  Here&#8217;s why:  even though all of the major stock averages are still below the 61.8% retracement there is one index that has blown through it &#8212; the Transports.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Transports1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7247" title="Transports" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Transports1-300x196.png" alt="" width="300" height="196" /></a></p>
<p>The above chart is a bullish indicator of things to come.  The other indexes should follow the lead of the Transports.  It will be interesting to see if the Transportation index can exceed the 78.6% level.  Not always, but quite frequently, when the 78.6% level is exceeded the rally will move 100% of the prior move.</p>
<p>Secondly, I know the basics of wave counting.  It isn&#8217;t a tool on which I rely, but I stay aware.  Using basic wave theory, the current swing should not violate the prior wave 1 down if the market is still correcting.  If it does violate the 1st wave down of the prior move then it&#8217;s very likely the market is making a fresh move to the upside.  Here&#8217;s a count on the S&amp;P chart &#8211;</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/SP-waves.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7248" title="S&amp;P waves" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/SP-waves-300x194.png" alt="" width="300" height="194" /></a></p>
<p>The Composite has the same look!</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/NAZ-waves.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7249" title="NAZ waves" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/NAZ-waves-300x196.png" alt="" width="300" height="196" /></a></p>
<h3>Bottom line for all stock traders and investors:  expect a minor pullback in the next few days.  The next retreat will provide a lot of information about the future path of price.  If the next pullback violates the 200d MA then I&#8217;ll have to stop and reconsider this mess.</h3>
<p>Stops have been updated on tonight&#8217;s trade sheet.  I&#8217;m hoping to bank some partial profits, soon.</p>
<p><a rel="nofollow" href="http://tiny.cc/2lobx">Trade Sheet</a></p>
