      <title>Range Trading</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/range-trading-4/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/range-trading-4/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Wed, 29 Jun 2011 04:05:18 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7232</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Today was a terrific range trading day! Each of the major averages followed yesterday&#8217;s move with another move up today.  Notice how price created a nice tall bar and closed at the top of the bar.  Very strong and bullish. &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/range-trading-4/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<h3>Today was a terrific range trading day!</h3>
<p>Each of the major averages followed yesterday&#8217;s move with another move up today.  Notice how price created a nice tall bar and closed at the top of the bar.  Very strong and bullish.</p>
<p>The S&amp;P 500 has started a channel of higher lows and higher highs.  Ideally I&#8217;d like to see the 1300 pivot level cleared on huge volume.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/SP5.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7233" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/SP5-300x216.png" alt="" width="300" height="216" /></a></p>
<p>The NASDAQ Composite has cleared the pivot area and broken above consolidation at the 200 d MA.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/NASDAQ3.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7234" title="NASDAQ" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/NASDAQ3-300x217.png" alt="" width="300" height="217" /></a></p>
<p>The only complaint about these charts is the lack of volume.   A big green bar as big as the last red volume bar would be strong confirmation that this market has the power to move higher.</p>
<p><span id="more-7232"></span>You can see that price is now trading well above the double green Range lines on this NASDAQ chart.  We need to see price stick above this area for the next few days.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Range-Lines1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7235" title="Range Lines" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Range-Lines1-300x289.png" alt="" width="300" height="289" /></a></p>
<p>The S&amp;P 500 is just barely above Range resistance, but that&#8217;s okay.  The junior averages have been paving the way for the seniors.</p>
<p>A quick look at a couple of the bellwether stocks shows that maybe a pause will be coming in the next day or so.  AAPL has moved up smartly, but done so on decreasing volume.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/AAPL5.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7236" title="AAPL" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/AAPL5-300x240.png" alt="" width="300" height="240" /></a></p>
<p>AMZN had a narrow price bar for the day and with small volume.  FCX on the other hand broke out of consolidation and above the 200 d MA on very good volume.</p>
<p>We&#8217;re not out of the woods yet.  The bears are still lurking and the market can fall victim to negative headlines.  Yet if we&#8217;re witnessing an early bull phase then other sector stocks, like FCX, will fall in line and start trading up, too.</p>
<h2>It&#8217;s a critical time.  Watch and see if price can hold its gains and continue range trading to higher levels.</h2>
<p>Tonight&#8217;s trade sheet shows the current, active trades.  I&#8217;m leaving GNTX on because it is still holding true to its pattern.</p>
<p>This trading environment is like walking on egg shells.  Each trade must be carefully placed.  Then it&#8217;s time to hope the market catches fire and lifts each position to profitability before stops are hit!</p>
<p><a href="http://tiny.cc/z8ur9">Wednesday&#8217;s Trade Sheet</a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
