      <title>One Day Wonder?</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/day-2/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/day-2/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Tue, 28 Jun 2011 02:40:17 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Trading The Market]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7222</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Recent market activity has found that one day the market climbs and the next day it tumbles.  That must come to an end if there&#8217;s to be a swing higher. AAPL and AMZN, two of the bellwether stocks didn&#8217;t disappoint &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/day-2/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Recent market activity has found that one day the market climbs and the next day it tumbles.  That must come to an end if there&#8217;s to be a swing higher.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/SP4.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7224" title="S&amp;P" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/SP4-300x210.png" alt="" width="300" height="210" /></a></p>
<p>AAPL and AMZN, two of the bellwether stocks didn&#8217;t disappoint and had a great day.  Both are likely part of the month/quarter end window-dressing.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/AAPL4.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7225" title="AAPL" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/AAPL4-300x210.png" alt="" width="300" height="210" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/AMZN1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7227" title="AMZN" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/AMZN1-300x212.png" alt="" width="300" height="212" /></a></p>
<p>Caution is warranted until the rest of the market catches up with the enthusiastic trading from the A-team.</p>
<p><span id="more-7222"></span>Today&#8217;s price action was wide-ranging, but volume was absent.  What is needed is a big volume push to confirm that price is moving up with the support of the professional traders.  Even though price is trading above the 200d MA the situation is still defensive.</p>
<p>Price must clear the double, horizontal, red, lines on this chart.  They mark Range resistance which has been a stubborn area to crack.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Range-Lines.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7228" title="Range Lines" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Range-Lines-300x228.png" alt="" width="300" height="228" /></a></p>
<p>A couple of new ideas are on tonight&#8217;s trade sheet along with those that are still holding their pattern.</p>
<p>Keep the position size small and obey the stops without question if you decide to jump into the trading pool.  There are still bears in the water!</p>
<p><a href="http://tinyurl.com/4d3tfoc">Trade Sheet</a></p>
]]></content:encoded>
