      <title>Charts, Data, Analysis For The Week Of June 27th</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/charts-data-analysis-week-june-27th/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/charts-data-analysis-week-june-27th/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sat, 25 Jun 2011 19:49:49 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[market analysis]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[stock charts]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[stock data]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7210</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[This was a very crazy week and a difficult market to track and analyze.  Just when the pattern looked obvious it changed into a different variety. The entire market is in a funk.  All of the sectors look very negative &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/charts-data-analysis-week-june-27th/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>This was a very crazy week and a difficult market to track and analyze.  Just when the pattern looked obvious it changed into a different variety.</p>
<p>The entire market is in a funk.  All of the sectors look very negative and show no sign of pulling out of this nose dive.</p>
<p>The point of concentration should narrow to the S&amp;P for it represents <em>the market.</em></p>
<p>What is clear are the two areas of pivot low and pivot high.  The direction price may trace is murky because it&#8217;s caught squarely between the the two pivots.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Pivots2.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7213" title="Pivots" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Pivots2-300x200.png" alt="" width="300" height="200" /></a></p>
<p>Yet I looked at this chart and wondered if Friday was a washout day for sellers?  The price bar has a large range from high to low and volume was enormous compared to the last few days.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Washout.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7214" title="Washout" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Washout-300x218.png" alt="" width="300" height="218" /></a></p>
<p>On the negative side, I see that price closed near the bottom of its range.  On the plus side, price didn&#8217;t make a lower low and the major averages are still trading above their 200d MAs.</p>
<p>Without a break of the higher pivot a fresh move to the upside is unlikely.  Break the lower pivot and all bets are off the table.  <span id="more-7210"></span></p>
<p><strong>Sector Action</strong></p>
<p>The S&amp;P was off -0.24 for the week.  The sectors performed like this:</p>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Metals and Mining  +4%</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Retail  2.7</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Materials  2.2</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Consumer Discretionary  1.4</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Industrials  0.51</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Oil and Gas  0.38</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Technology  0.37</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Healthcare  -0.26</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Utilities  0.58</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Financials  0.87</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Energy  -1</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Staples 1.7</span></address>
<address> </address>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Statistical Scans</strong></p>
<p>There is no trustworthy data from these scans.  Jerky price data is nearly impossible to analyze for profitable trades.</p>
<p><strong>The Bottom Line</strong></p>
<p>Transitional markets are tricky, but can be rewarding.  It looks like the S&amp;P has formed a broadening pattern called  a reverse symmetrical triangle or an expanding triangle.  Whatever you want to call it this pattern is usually found at tops and bottoms.  It is a bit dicey to trade.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Expanding-Triangle.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7216" title="Expanding Triangle" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Expanding-Triangle-300x254.png" alt="" width="300" height="254" /></a></p>
<p>If the pattern does transition to a bullish move the push can be explosive.  Trying to get in ahead of the move can mean frequent small losses so be prepared.   AG is an example &#8212; entered Thursday got stopped on Friday.</p>
<p>The key is to keep the losses <strong>small.</strong> Once filled make sure an order is entered to sell at the stop price.</p>
<p>Window dressing is on tap for next week as the month and quarter come to a close.  Housing data is the headline that may unnerve the market, yet everyone that pays attention knows that the housing sector is in bad shape.</p>
<p>Watch and see if the market will start and shake off the bad news as it did earlier this past week with the headlines coming from  Greece.</p>
<p>I think a few long trades are worth a try.  The ideas are on the trade sheet.</p>
<p>Have a good weekend!</p>
<p><a href="http://tinyurl.com/4d3tfoc">Trade Sheet</a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
