    <item>
      <title>Reading The Tea Leaves Of The Tape</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/reading-tea-leaves/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/reading-tea-leaves/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Fri, 24 Jun 2011 01:57:41 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Stock Market]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[stock market tape reading]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7199</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[photo credit: allaboutgeorge The futures were flashing red late last night and held their color this morning. The open was especially grim.  Yet there are clues the smart money is getting into position. As the broad market took a beating &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/reading-tea-leaves/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><a title="Tea leaves" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/35034347485@N01/4142791697/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2560/4142791697_c5e11a694d_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Tea leaves" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><small> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="allaboutgeorge" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/35034347485@N01/4142791697/" target="_blank">allaboutgeorge</a></small></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">The futures were flashing red late last night and held their color this morning.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">The open was especially grim.  Yet there are clues the smart money is getting into position.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">As the broad market took a beating AAPL found its footing and leaped off an old support level.  This is <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/current-market-news/charts-data-analysis-week-june-20th/">a clue</a> that should not be ignored.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/AAPL3.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7200" title="AAPL" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/AAPL3-300x258.png" alt="" width="300" height="258" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span id="more-7199"></span>If we follow more clues to this market&#8217;s behavior we should look at some Fibonacci relationships.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">The decline started on May 2nd.  So far, the low of the move came on June 16th when price clipped the 200d MA and the median line, here &#8211;</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/SP-5009.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7201" title="S&amp;P 500" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/SP-5009-300x179.png" alt="" width="300" height="179" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Using the S&amp;P as an example, price has formed a pivot low (June 16)  and a pivot high (yesterday&#8217;s high at 1298).  Last night I mentioned that price needed to get above 1300ish to give some assurance that the down move has ended.  Here&#8217;s why:</p>
<p style="text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;">1.  Price must exceed the pivot high at 1298</p>
<p style="text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;">2.  The Fibonacci relationship of 38.2% is tantalizingly close to the 1300 level.  This is a minimum retrace level</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Here&#8217;s the chart with the Fib lines &#8211;</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/SP-50010.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7202" title="S&amp;P 500" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/SP-50010-300x179.png" alt="" width="300" height="179" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Will price cross the pivot high and the 1300ish level?  I kind of think so, here&#8217;s why &#8211;</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Clue #1  The way AAPL is acting is hopeful.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Clue #2  The Transports have already pierced the critical level and did it on big volume.  Here&#8217;s the chart &#8211;</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Transports.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7203" title="Transports" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Transports-300x178.png" alt="" width="300" height="178" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Clue #3  The junior averages are starting to fall in step with the seniors and the chart patterns are beginning to have a similar look.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Out of the slew of trade ideas only one was purchased.  Not unusual given the type of day.  There are 11 ideas on tonight&#8217;s sheet &#8212; a few are repeats from last night.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://tinyurl.com/4d3tfoc">Trade Sheet</a></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
