      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7196</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[The RSI from last night looked like it was confronting a brick wall.  Sure enough equities fell victim to eager sellers late in the session. With the end of the month end of the quarter fast approaching fund managers will &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/trading-the-market/nights-rsi-pegged-todays-decline/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The RSI from last night looked like it was confronting a brick wall.  Sure enough equities fell victim to eager sellers late in the session.</p>
<p>With the end of the month end of the quarter fast approaching fund managers will want to see higher prices.  The S&amp;P needs to get past 1300 to make their dreams come true.</p>
<p>The bears still have control and the defense is still on the field.  Today&#8217;s price probe was but a point above yesterday&#8217;s high.  Caution is the watch word when contemplating long trades.</p>
<p><span id="more-7196"></span>Nothing ventured, nothing gained.  It seems the time has come to try a few longs.</p>
<p>Don&#8217;t go crazy, be a bit careful with the trade ideas I&#8217;ve posted.  You&#8217;ll find an eclectic collection of a drug stock, a few silver plays, and an idea or two from the oil patch.</p>
<p>This market has shown signs that it wants to shrug off bad news and head higher.  Today&#8217;s late afternoon selling may have given us an entry for tomorrow.</p>
<p>Futures look a bit negative as I post this ( 9:30 Pacific Time).  That&#8217;s fine.  If the market opens lower, but closes higher then it will be another sign that price wants to climb.</p>
<p><a href="http://tinyurl.com/4d3tfoc">Trade Sheet</a></p>
