    <item>
      <title>No Easy Trading Solutions, Yet</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/easy-trading-solutions/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/easy-trading-solutions/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Mon, 20 Jun 2011 23:43:30 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[range trading]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Stock Market]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[trading solutions]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7185</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[There are no easy trading solutions.  The market indexes are not agreeing with each other.  The lack of consensus makes the job of defining a clear direction a bit harder. Broadly speaking the senior and junior averages are not in &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/easy-trading-solutions/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<h1>There are no easy trading solutions.  The market indexes are not agreeing with each other.  The lack of consensus makes the job of defining a clear direction a bit harder.</h1>
<p>Broadly speaking the senior and junior averages are not in sync.  The seniors (S&amp;P 500, DJ-30) are more bullish than the juniors (NASDAQ Composite, Russell 2000).</p>
<p>The S&amp;P has traded up for the last three days after bouncing on the 200d moving average.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/SP-5007.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7186" title="S&amp;P 500" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/SP-5007-300x197.png" alt="" width="300" height="197" /></a></p>
<p>Not the NASDAQ Composite.  It is still trading below the 200d moving average and has yet to make a higher high and a higher low.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/NASDAQ2.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7187" title="NASDAQ" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/NASDAQ2-300x198.png" alt="" width="300" height="198" /></a></p>
<h2>Both indexes are trying to work off their oversold status.  Until both the blue chips and small stock indexes come to an agreement and start making higher highs and higher lows there will be no easy trading solutions.</h2>
<p><span id="more-7185"></span>Another troubling aspect is volume.  Today it was almost non-existent.  Not a good sign if looking for a new bull phase.  Volume is not confirming the higher highs and higher lows.</p>
<p>Yesterday&#8217;s big volume bar looks like short-covering, bargain hunting, and technical buying.  The lack of follow through today shows me the smart money is not participating.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/SP-5008.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7188" title="S&amp;P 500" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/SP-5008-300x252.png" alt="" width="300" height="252" /></a></p>
<p>The absence of volume may also be in anticipation of the Fed&#8217;s meeting which starts tomorrow.</p>
<p>Let&#8217;s give it a couple of days and see if there is a retest of the lows.  It we get a retest and the recent lows hold that&#8217;s a good time to try a cautious long trade.  If a down move breaks the old lows and bounces that will be a good time to try a long trade, too.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m watching the energy space for long ideas.  Many of the stocks have seem to found a ledge of support.  Whether they can stay on the ledge is the question.  Take a look at ATPG, BAS, and CIE and you&#8217;ll see what I mean.</p>
<p>The short side still looks like it has possibilities, too. AXP and COF look tempting, but I&#8217;ll pass for now and hold the ones on the trade sheet.</p>
<p><a href="http://tinyurl.com/4d3tfoc">Trade Sheet</a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
