      <title>Charts, Data, Analysis For The Week Of June 20th</title>
      <link>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/charts-data-analysis-week-june-20th/</link>
      <comments>http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/charts-data-analysis-week-june-20th/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sat, 18 Jun 2011 19:35:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Range Trader</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Range Lines]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[range trading]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Stock Market]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Technical Analysis]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7160</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[There is no new information that changes the market&#8217;s bearish complexion.  In fact, there&#8217;s information to bolster the bearish case. When a bellwether stock like Apple starts to form a broadening top it may be giving a clue that the &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/charts-data-analysis-week-june-20th/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>There is no new information that changes the market&#8217;s bearish complexion.  In fact, there&#8217;s information to bolster the bearish case.</p>
<p>When a bellwether stock like Apple starts to form a broadening top it may be giving a clue that the smart money is selling.  AAPL has been pressured and couldn&#8217;t find its legs even when the market tried to rally late in the week.</p>
<p>Apple has superior fundamentals and is a beloved stock.  When it can&#8217;t find its way higher it should be a warning (chart follows below).</p>
<p>These are the bellwether stocks and their respective charts: AAPL, FCX, GOOG, GS.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/AAPL1.png"></a><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/AAPL2.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7166" title="AAPL" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/AAPL2-300x264.png" alt="" width="300" height="264" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/FCX1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7167" title="FCX" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/FCX1-300x264.png" alt="" width="300" height="264" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/GOOG1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7168" title="GOOG" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/GOOG1-300x262.png" alt="" width="300" height="262" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/GS1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7169" title="GS" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/GS1-300x262.png" alt="" width="300" height="262" /></a></p>
<p>These are the major indexes with pitchforks and moving averages.  Notice how well the bullish pitchfork (green) contained price.  It looks like the bearish fork (blue) is accurate, too.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/NASDAQ1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7170" title="NASDAQ" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/NASDAQ1-300x199.png" alt="" width="300" height="199" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/DJ-302.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7171" title="DJ-30" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/DJ-302-300x198.png" alt="" width="300" height="198" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/RUT1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7172" title="RUT" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/RUT1-300x199.png" alt="" width="300" height="199" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/SP-5006.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7173" title="S&amp;P 500" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/SP-5006-300x197.png" alt="" width="300" height="197" /></a></p>
<p>Watch the disposition of price at the 200d moving average this week.  That average will either hold price or it won&#8217;t.</p>
<p>I find no compelling evidence to trade this market from the long side.  Scouting for short trades or staying in cash are likely the best options for now.</p>
<p><em>Premium content beyond this point including a new feature &#8212; a Heat Map.  The Heat Map shows the broad market&#8217;s condition at a glance.  Drill down into each column and the specific price patterns, critical moving average conditions, the disposition of the market timer, and range line levels to watch are clearly noted.  Membership information is on the sidebar to the right.</em></p>
<p><span id="more-7160"></span></p>
<p>This heat map will quickly reveal the inclination of the market: red is bearish, green is bullish, and yellow is neutral.  A closer look at the contents reveals some important levels to watch in the coming week.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Heat-Map2.png"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-7175" title="Heat Map" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Heat-Map2-1024x114.png" alt="" width="725" height="80" /></a></p>
<p><strong>Sector Performance:</strong></p>
<p>The S&amp;P eked out a .04% gain this week.  The sectors performed like this:</p>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Retail  +2.2%</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Consumer Staples  0.74</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Industrials  0.68</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Financials  0.40</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Consumer Discretionary  0.24</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #008000;">Utilities  0.06</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Health Care  -0.11</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Technology  1.29</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Energy  2.24</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Materials  2.53</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Oil and Gas  2.9</span></address>
<address><span style="color: #ff0000;">Metals and Mining 4.0</span></address>
<p><strong>Statistical Scans:</strong></p>
<p>These scans produced no sound set-ups from the long side.</p>
<p>So far, the correct trade in this market has been from the short side.  In this type of market environment it&#8217;s necessary to go through the charts one at a time.  Statistical scanning is of little help because short-trading is much quicker than long trades which follow a trend.</p>
<p>The current trade ideas are working and are the best set-ups I&#8217;ve seen for high probability success ( 3 out of 4 isn&#8217;t bad).   Most of the financials look really sick, but the financial stocks on the Trade Sheet got a little ahead of themselves and were ripe for a short.</p>
<p>I&#8217;ve looked at hundreds of charts in the financial sector, but don&#8217;t see anything I like any better than what we already have.</p>
<p>American Express (AXP) did make me look a second time.  To help you see what I see here&#8217;s the daily chart.  Looks good, huh?</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/AXP.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7177" title="AXP" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/AXP-300x199.png" alt="" width="300" height="199" /></a></p>
<p>This is the hourly chart of AXP.  Two things that stop me from trading this one short are: price is trading above the top fork line and price has consolidated for several bars.  This one doesn&#8217;t have the same potential reward as our current flock.  It may very well fall and make a good short, but I&#8217;m going to take a pass.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/AXPh.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7178" title="AXPh" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/AXPh-300x190.png" alt="" width="300" height="190" /></a></p>
<p>An interesting week lies ahead.  Home sales are reported early in the week and the FOMC starts its meeting on Tuesday.  Events look dicey in Europe as Greece is again front and center.</p>
<p>The Trade Sheet follows.  Have a good weekend and I&#8217;ll see you back here soon!</p>
<p><a href="http://tinyurl.com/4d3tfoc">Trade Sheet</a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
