      <category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/?p=7137</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Today&#8217;s trading was more of the same stuff the stock market has been feeding us all week.  I&#8217;ll be glad when options expiration is in the rear view mirror.  Not that it will make much difference. The juniors NASDAQ Composite &#8230; <a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/uncategorized/thursdays-leftovers/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Today&#8217;s trading was more of the same stuff the stock market has been feeding us all week.  I&#8217;ll be glad when options expiration is in the rear view mirror.  Not that it will make much difference.</p>
<p>The juniors NASDAQ Composite and brother NDX closed below the 200d MA yesterday and never rose above it today.  Volume was moderate on both indexes.  Price is still trading at the median line (blue dashed line), but this isn&#8217;t a hopeful sign if we want to find a floor.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/NAZ1.png"><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/NAZ2.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7139" title="NAZ" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/NAZ2-300x287.png" alt="" width="300" height="287" /></a></a></p>
<p>The S&amp;P 500 has the same look, but hasn&#8217;t closed below the 200.  Yet the lower lows keep appearing at each night&#8217;s close.</p>
<p>The US dollar is probing new highs.  It crossed the median line and closed above it.  Likely that old bucky is headed for the 200d MA, but coming at it from the underside is much more bullish.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/US-dollar1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-7140" title="US dollar" src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/US-dollar1-300x291.png" alt="" width="300" height="291" /></a></p>
<p>Members have been short-trading selected financials and doing well.  75% of the trades have banked money and we&#8217;re still holding partial positions.</p>
<p>Until this market changes character I see no reason to anticipate long trades any time soon.</p>
<p><span id="more-7137"></span>Keep holding on to those shorts.  The headlines continue to be gloomy and if there&#8217;s to be a catalyst for this market to rise I&#8217;m perplexed as to what it may be.</p>
<p><a href="http://tinyurl.com/4d3tfoc">Trade Sheet</a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
