      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><a title="Sleepy Time" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/56846427@N02/5626432575/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5066/5626432575_69eb16c730_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Sleepy Time" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="chadskeers" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/56846427@N02/5626432575/" target="_blank">chadskeers</a></small></p>
<p>Nothing comes to mind.</p>
<p>There was no positive information that I saw which would account for the lift in the market.</p>
<p>The 200d MA has proved a horizontal ledge.  Both the NASDAQ Composite and Russell 2000 tested it.  The S&amp;P 500 never quite got to the 200.</p>
<p>Volume was puny on each of the major averages.  Follow through will be key.<span id="more-7129"></span>The market needs to clear some pivots to prove a floor has been built under price.  1294 is the first critical pivot.</p>
<p>The financials proved good short ideas for today.  I&#8217;ll kick back and see what happens.</p>
<p>There will be plenty of times to build long positions if this market proves itself.  If not, a few shorts may come in handy especially if the market breaks the 200d MA.  Breaking that level may create the panic selling that would wash out the weak hands.  The 200d MA and the March low are widely watched.  The algorithms will likely kick in if either one of those points are breached.</p>
<p>Updated Trade Sheet is <a href="http://tinyurl.com/4d3tfoc">HERE.</a></p>
