<p style="text-align: center;"><small><a title="Attribution License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.rangetraders.com/blog/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="Fillmore Photography" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/74321854@N00/2306147412/" target="_blank">Fillmore Photography</a></small></p>
<p>The opening strength attracted sellers into the fray and the market did little to acquit itself.</p>
<p>The S&amp;P is close to a natural support ledge ( 200d MA).  If this widely recognized barrier falls look out below.  An oversold market that fails to rally is extremely vulnerable to emotional sell-offs creating a &#8220;sell now ask questions later&#8221; type of carnage.</p>
<p>Lots of economic data later this week could propel the market in either direction.  Watch closely the reaction to bad news.  If the market can absorb a body blow of bad news and still stand it may be a sign that it has found a level from which to form a base.</p>
<p><span id="more-7125"></span>It looks like the time has finally arrived.  A slew of short set-ups are on tonight&#8217;s trade sheet.  Many have had a multi-day retrace from lower levels and are now crowding the RSI 50 line.</p>
<p>Honor the stops and don&#8217;t bet the farm, but these look very tempting:</p>
